WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.501 --> 00:00:03.503
(drumroll)

2
00:00:05.505 --> 00:00:08.341
(rousing orchestral fanfare playing)

3
00:00:19.477 --> 00:00:21.312
(fanfare ends)

4
00:00:23.440 --> 00:00:25.316
(wind gusting)

5
00:00:32.449 --> 00:00:34.325
(wind whistling)

6
00:00:47.130 --> 00:00:49.174
(thunder rumbles in distance)

7
00:00:54.763 --> 00:00:56.848
(thunder cracks)

8
00:01:03.563 --> 00:01:05.565
(thunder crackling, rumbling)

9
00:01:08.777 --> 00:01:10.862
(thunder fades)

10
00:01:26.586 --> 00:01:28.379
(low rumbling, getting louder)

11
00:01:56.407 --> 00:01:58.243
(crackling, rumbling)

12
00:02:21.808 --> 00:02:23.935
(resolute sigh)

13
00:02:47.041 --> 00:02:48.376
Zeus.

14
00:02:53.506 --> 00:02:54.757
Poseidon.

15
00:02:55.842 --> 00:02:57.385
It's been many years.

16
00:03:01.431 --> 00:03:03.266
What do you see?

17
00:03:07.312 --> 00:03:08.813
Thunderclouds.

18
00:03:11.232 --> 00:03:13.109
But no lightning.

19
00:03:15.695 --> 00:03:16.738
Stolen.

20
00:03:20.366 --> 00:03:21.367
What?

21
00:03:21.451 --> 00:03:22.911
You think I took it?

22
00:03:24.037 --> 00:03:26.915
Omnipotence has
blinded you, brother.

23
00:03:26.998 --> 00:03:29.626
We are forbidden from
stealing each other's powers.

24
00:03:31.669 --> 00:03:33.379
But our children aren't.

25
00:03:34.964 --> 00:03:36.257
You're accusing my son?

26
00:03:37.759 --> 00:03:39.969
I haven't seen him
since he was a baby.

27
00:03:40.053 --> 00:03:43.223
He doesn't know me or even know
who he is because of you.

28
00:03:43.306 --> 00:03:45.016
If your son is the thief...

29
00:03:46.100 --> 00:03:48.436
I will send him
to the depths of Tartarus.

30
00:03:49.520 --> 00:03:50.772
If you touch him...

31
00:03:51.773 --> 00:03:53.733
you will have the fight of your life.

32
00:03:57.820 --> 00:03:59.948
You must return the bolt to me.

33
00:04:00.949 --> 00:04:05.453
In 14 days, by midnight
on the summer solstice.

34
00:04:12.460 --> 00:04:14.337
Or there will be war.

35
00:04:38.736 --> 00:04:40.655
(water sloshing, bubbling)

36
00:05:54.062 --> 00:05:56.564
BOY: And he's alive!
(laughs)

37
00:05:56.647 --> 00:05:58.649
(clapping)

38
00:05:58.733 --> 00:06:00.902
Percy Jackson is a beast!

39
00:06:00.985 --> 00:06:03.029
You're a beast, man!
Give me some.

40
00:06:03.112 --> 00:06:04.906
(chuckles)

41
00:06:04.989 --> 00:06:05.990
How long was that?

42
00:06:06.074 --> 00:06:07.950
-Seven minutes.
-Seven minutes?

43
00:06:08.034 --> 00:06:09.243
-Mm-hmm.
-Oh.

44
00:06:09.327 --> 00:06:11.579
That's crazy, man.
That's ridiculous.

45
00:06:11.662 --> 00:06:14.665
-How do you do it?
-I just like being in water.

46
00:06:14.749 --> 00:06:17.335
(sighs)
It's the one place I can think.

47
00:06:17.418 --> 00:06:18.795
Mm-hmm.

48
00:06:21.631 --> 00:06:23.674
(students chattering)

49
00:06:26.344 --> 00:06:29.597
(school bell rings)

50
00:06:31.307 --> 00:06:33.810
Wow, wish I could spend all day
underwater instead of this place.

51
00:06:33.893 --> 00:06:36.604
Right? It's like high school
without the musical.

52
00:06:37.688 --> 00:06:40.233
Every day is the same thing.
Look at this.

53
00:06:40.316 --> 00:06:41.901
(sighs)

54
00:06:48.699 --> 00:06:50.201
Good morning.

55
00:06:50.284 --> 00:06:53.496
I'm Miss Dodds,
your substitute English teacher.

56
00:06:54.080 --> 00:06:56.582
Would someone please explain
what Shakespeare was trying

57
00:06:56.666 --> 00:06:58.751
to convey in this line from <i>Othello?</i>

58
00:07:02.255 --> 00:07:03.714
Percy Jackson?

59
00:07:09.137 --> 00:07:10.179
MISS DODDS: Well?

60
00:07:18.521 --> 00:07:20.064
I'm sorry. I don't know.

61
00:07:22.191 --> 00:07:23.693
Anybody else?

62
00:07:29.532 --> 00:07:31.492
MAN: Yo, buddy,
you can't park there!

63
00:07:33.453 --> 00:07:35.455
(laughs)
It was so funny.

64
00:07:35.538 --> 00:07:37.331
That's great.
I didn't even know about it.

65
00:07:37.415 --> 00:07:38.708
MAN 2:
It's not my problem, all right?

66
00:07:38.791 --> 00:07:40.251
Look, there's nothing I can do.

67
00:07:40.334 --> 00:07:43.087
You call them... you call them
and see what the problem is, all right?

68
00:07:43.171 --> 00:07:44.422
MAN 3: Yeah, yeah...

69
00:07:44.505 --> 00:07:46.090
PERCY:
Hey, Mom, I'm home.

70
00:07:46.174 --> 00:07:47.550
MOM:
I'm up here, honey.

71
00:07:49.135 --> 00:07:50.136
Hi.

72
00:07:50.219 --> 00:07:51.220
Hey, Mom.

73
00:07:51.304 --> 00:07:53.389
-How was school today?
-The usual.

74
00:07:54.724 --> 00:07:59.020
Think this, uh,
dyslexia thing is getting worse.

75
00:07:59.103 --> 00:08:00.938
Oh, why do you think that?

76
00:08:02.064 --> 00:08:06.027
(sighs) I don't know.
Maybe it's the ADHD.

77
00:08:07.528 --> 00:08:10.698
You know, I thought this school
was supposed to make things better.

78
00:08:10.781 --> 00:08:13.159
Percy, I know how hard this is for you.

79
00:08:14.076 --> 00:08:16.120
But someday it'll all make sense.

80
00:08:16.204 --> 00:08:19.081
Really? When?

81
00:08:19.165 --> 00:08:20.541
Hmm?

82
00:08:20.625 --> 00:08:22.210
Tonight, tomorrow? When?

83
00:08:23.169 --> 00:08:24.295
(door closes)

84
00:08:24.378 --> 00:08:25.922
Woman!

85
00:08:26.923 --> 00:08:28.883
-Hi, Gabe.
-(Gabe groans)

86
00:08:28.966 --> 00:08:30.384
Where's my beer?

87
00:08:30.968 --> 00:08:32.595
It's in the fridge.

88
00:08:32.678 --> 00:08:37.016
So, what, it's supposed to magically float
from the icebox and into my hand?

89
00:08:37.099 --> 00:08:38.518
(chuckles)

90
00:08:38.601 --> 00:08:39.936
Hustle. (chuckles)

91
00:08:40.019 --> 00:08:42.522
Oh, come on, man.
You have to do that right here?

92
00:08:42.605 --> 00:08:45.399
It's disgusting. W-We're in a kitchen.

93
00:08:47.693 --> 00:08:49.362
Yeah, real charmer you got there.

94
00:08:49.445 --> 00:08:50.488
Really.

95
00:08:50.571 --> 00:08:52.031
Show some respect.

96
00:08:52.114 --> 00:08:53.824
All right?
That's my mom right there.

97
00:08:54.909 --> 00:08:56.744
(grunts)

98
00:09:03.251 --> 00:09:04.794
GABE: This is my house.

99
00:09:06.295 --> 00:09:08.422
You show some respect.

100
00:09:09.173 --> 00:09:10.716
Oh, come on.

101
00:09:12.718 --> 00:09:16.264
Why do you stay with that pig?
He smells like a sewer.

102
00:09:16.347 --> 00:09:19.267
He sleeps till noon every day,
and he can't even hold a job.

103
00:09:19.350 --> 00:09:21.060
Why do you stay with him?

104
00:09:24.063 --> 00:09:27.400
He's been good to us, Percy,
in ways you just... you don't understand.

105
00:09:28.901 --> 00:09:30.278
You're right.

106
00:09:30.361 --> 00:09:31.862
I don't understand. I don't get it.

107
00:09:40.538 --> 00:09:42.623
(sighs heavily)

108
00:09:46.085 --> 00:09:48.087
(people conversing indistinctly)

109
00:10:00.308 --> 00:10:02.226
POSEIDON: <i>Be prepared.</i>

110
00:10:02.310 --> 00:10:05.354
<i>Everything is about to change, Percy.</i>

111
00:10:05.438 --> 00:10:08.274
<i>Everything is about to change.</i>

112
00:10:17.491 --> 00:10:19.452
MR. BRUNNER:
There are 12 Olympian gods.

113
00:10:20.745 --> 00:10:25.958
The Big Three are the brothers
Zeus, Poseidon, and Hades.

114
00:10:26.042 --> 00:10:31.130
They attained power by
overthrowing their father, Cronus,

115
00:10:31.714 --> 00:10:33.174
chopping him into little pieces.

116
00:10:35.635 --> 00:10:39.096
The three gods
have been rivals ever since.

117
00:10:39.180 --> 00:10:40.640
Always arguing.

118
00:10:40.723 --> 00:10:42.933
Always threatening war.

119
00:10:43.517 --> 00:10:47.813
On several occasions, they would
come down to Earth and, um...

120
00:10:49.565 --> 00:10:50.900
how shall I put this?

121
00:10:50.983 --> 00:10:52.276
Hook up?

122
00:10:52.360 --> 00:10:54.111
(laughter)

123
00:10:54.195 --> 00:10:56.530
They would hook up with mortals.

124
00:10:56.614 --> 00:11:01.452
The children of these unions
were half god, half human.

125
00:11:02.536 --> 00:11:05.164
Can anyone tell me
what they were called?

126
00:11:05.247 --> 00:11:06.499
Percy.

127
00:11:07.500 --> 00:11:08.668
(whispering) Percy.

128
00:11:09.669 --> 00:11:11.921
Oh, I'm sorry. What?
What, Mr. Brunner?

129
00:11:13.798 --> 00:11:19.136
What is the proper name of
the offspring of a human and a god?

130
00:11:20.846 --> 00:11:22.098
Demigod.

131
00:11:22.181 --> 00:11:23.307
Exactly.

132
00:11:23.891 --> 00:11:26.560
And many became great heroes,

133
00:11:26.644 --> 00:11:30.106
like Hercules and Achilles.

134
00:11:30.189 --> 00:11:34.402
Can you name... another?

135
00:11:36.654 --> 00:11:37.947
I'll give you a hint.

136
00:11:38.948 --> 00:11:41.033
You have something in common.

137
00:11:51.335 --> 00:11:52.545
Percy.

138
00:11:55.172 --> 00:11:56.424
Perseus?

139
00:11:59.593 --> 00:12:00.803
Correct.

140
00:12:02.012 --> 00:12:04.598
Now, over here, we have a depiction

141
00:12:04.682 --> 00:12:07.852
of Hercules defeating the Nemean lion.

142
00:12:08.853 --> 00:12:12.565
Hercules killed the beast
with his bare hands

143
00:12:12.648 --> 00:12:15.359
and took the skin as a trophy.

144
00:12:15.443 --> 00:12:17.194
Percy.

145
00:12:17.278 --> 00:12:19.155
Yes, Miss Dodds?

146
00:12:19.238 --> 00:12:20.781
We need to talk.

147
00:12:22.950 --> 00:12:23.951
Okay.

148
00:12:24.034 --> 00:12:28.080
BRUNNER: The next 11 labors
would become increasingly difficult.

149
00:12:28.164 --> 00:12:30.916
It would take Hercules three months...

150
00:12:38.758 --> 00:12:40.843
So, did I do something wrong?

151
00:12:43.304 --> 00:12:44.430
Miss Dodds?

152
00:12:45.431 --> 00:12:47.391
Hello?

153
00:12:47.475 --> 00:12:49.268
MISS DODDS (angrily):
Where is it?

154
00:12:49.351 --> 00:12:51.187
Whoa, whoa. Hey, hey.

155
00:12:51.270 --> 00:12:54.398
How... did you get up there?

156
00:12:54.482 --> 00:12:56.025
-(growls)
-Whoa! Whoa!

157
00:12:56.108 --> 00:12:58.486
(shrieking)

158
00:12:58.569 --> 00:13:00.946
(gasping, screams)

159
00:13:03.032 --> 00:13:05.326
-(gasps)
-You stole the lightning bolt.

160
00:13:05.409 --> 00:13:06.786
I don't know
what you're talking about!

161
00:13:06.869 --> 00:13:08.245
Give it to me.

162
00:13:08.329 --> 00:13:10.414
Whoa! Whoa!

163
00:13:10.498 --> 00:13:12.041
Give it to me.

164
00:13:12.124 --> 00:13:13.709
Now.

165
00:13:13.793 --> 00:13:15.711
Or I will bite your heart out.

166
00:13:15.795 --> 00:13:17.129
Percy!

167
00:13:17.213 --> 00:13:18.798
(gasping)

168
00:13:18.881 --> 00:13:19.799
Release him!

169
00:13:19.882 --> 00:13:21.592
You.

170
00:13:21.675 --> 00:13:25.471
Release him, or I swear
I'll tear you to pieces.

171
00:13:25.554 --> 00:13:27.306
(shrieking)

172
00:13:27.389 --> 00:13:28.808
Whoa!

173
00:13:28.891 --> 00:13:32.144
(groaning)

174
00:13:32.228 --> 00:13:34.146
(shrieking)

175
00:13:36.106 --> 00:13:37.566
(gasping)
Oh... oh...!

176
00:13:37.650 --> 00:13:39.360
Whoa, I'm going crazy!

177
00:13:39.443 --> 00:13:41.070
Oh... I should be on medication.

178
00:13:41.153 --> 00:13:42.738
-Percy, calm down, okay?
-I should be on medication.

179
00:13:42.822 --> 00:13:44.448
-Everything's going to be okay.
-Oh, God, wait.

180
00:13:44.532 --> 00:13:48.118
Did that really just happen?

181
00:13:48.202 --> 00:13:49.703
She just turned into that thing?

182
00:13:49.787 --> 00:13:54.124
A Fury... concealed in our school.
I should've known.

183
00:13:54.208 --> 00:13:57.253
Wait, a Fury? What's a Fury?

184
00:13:57.336 --> 00:13:59.004
And why did you say
you could tear her to pieces?

185
00:13:59.088 --> 00:14:01.048
What did she want from you?

186
00:14:01.131 --> 00:14:04.301
She... said something...

187
00:14:04.385 --> 00:14:06.136
about me...

188
00:14:06.387 --> 00:14:08.556
stealing a lightning bolt.

189
00:14:09.640 --> 00:14:10.683
They found him.

190
00:14:14.144 --> 00:14:15.312
He's in danger.

191
00:14:15.396 --> 00:14:16.772
-Who found me?
-Shh.

192
00:14:16.856 --> 00:14:19.233
-He's no longer secure here.
-Okay, where should we move him?

193
00:14:19.316 --> 00:14:20.734
We have no choice-- to the camp.

194
00:14:20.818 --> 00:14:23.279
Huh? What camp?
Look, I'm standing right here.

195
00:14:23.362 --> 00:14:25.114
If they think he's the thief,

196
00:14:25.197 --> 00:14:27.324
there's nowhere safe
on Heaven and Earth for him now.

197
00:14:27.408 --> 00:14:30.744
Percy, take this to defend yourself.

198
00:14:30.828 --> 00:14:34.540
It's a powerful weapon.
Guard it well.

199
00:14:34.623 --> 00:14:38.419
Only use it in times of severe distress.

200
00:14:40.421 --> 00:14:43.382
This is a pen. This is a pen!

201
00:14:43.465 --> 00:14:46.343
Take him to his mother.
And don't let him out of your sight.

202
00:14:46.427 --> 00:14:47.636
Okay. Percy, come on.

203
00:14:47.720 --> 00:14:49.305
Come on, man. Come on!

204
00:14:49.388 --> 00:14:50.598
-Are you guys crazy?
-Let's go!

205
00:14:50.681 --> 00:14:52.349
This is a pen, man.

206
00:14:52.433 --> 00:14:54.935
-Can't do anything with this.
-Come on!

207
00:14:55.019 --> 00:14:56.395
Look, man, what's going on?

208
00:14:56.478 --> 00:14:59.189
Shh! Look, don't
trust anyone, okay?

209
00:14:59.273 --> 00:15:01.775
Don't look at anybody.
Just keep walking!

210
00:15:01.859 --> 00:15:03.819
Why did Mr. Brunner
ask you to watch me?

211
00:15:03.903 --> 00:15:05.029
Because I'm your protector.

212
00:15:05.112 --> 00:15:07.531
Wait, wait, wait. Hold up.
My protector? Are you kidding?

213
00:15:07.615 --> 00:15:11.076
What? You think because I'm like this,
I'm not capable of keeping you safe?

214
00:15:11.160 --> 00:15:14.121
Maybe you're not seeing
what I'm seeing. You have crutches.

215
00:15:14.204 --> 00:15:16.582
Look, I would give my life
to secure your well-being.

216
00:15:16.665 --> 00:15:18.000
What are you talking about?
What's going on?

217
00:15:18.083 --> 00:15:21.170
We gotta warn your mom.
Come on, Perce.

218
00:15:21.253 --> 00:15:23.005
Come on!

219
00:15:24.089 --> 00:15:25.090
Sally!

220
00:15:25.174 --> 00:15:26.842
-PERCY: Mom!
-More beer!

221
00:15:26.926 --> 00:15:30.512
Hey, Mom, Mom, Mom, Mom,
look, we got to talk, okay?

222
00:15:30.596 --> 00:15:34.266
Hey! Can't you see she's
servicing me and my friends?

223
00:15:34.350 --> 00:15:37.895
Hey, hey! Don't talk about my mom
like that, you bald-headed freak.

224
00:15:37.978 --> 00:15:41.273
-No, Gabe! Gabe!
-Calm down!

225
00:15:41.357 --> 00:15:43.943
(grunting and groaning)

226
00:15:44.026 --> 00:15:45.569
-Oh, God.
-MAN: Whoa!

227
00:15:45.653 --> 00:15:46.820
Hey, nice one.

228
00:15:46.904 --> 00:15:48.989
Like I said, I'm your protector.

229
00:15:49.990 --> 00:15:51.700
Yeah.

230
00:15:51.784 --> 00:15:53.911
Sally, Percy has to leave now.

231
00:15:53.994 --> 00:15:55.746
Like, right now.

232
00:16:01.835 --> 00:16:03.671
PERCY:
Look, what is happening?

233
00:16:03.754 --> 00:16:06.298
Okay, I swear I didn't steal anything.

234
00:16:06.382 --> 00:16:09.885
Honey, I believe you. I believe you.

235
00:16:09.969 --> 00:16:12.137
Where are you taking me?
What is this camp?

236
00:16:12.221 --> 00:16:14.640
It's a camp for really special people.

237
00:16:14.723 --> 00:16:16.058
Like you.

238
00:16:16.141 --> 00:16:19.103
"Special people"?
What, am I crazy or something?

239
00:16:19.186 --> 00:16:20.980
SALLY: No, honey, no.

240
00:16:21.981 --> 00:16:23.983
Percy, this is about your father.

241
00:16:29.238 --> 00:16:30.531
SALLY:
...out of school, and I was working

242
00:16:30.614 --> 00:16:32.866
at the Jersey Shore when we first met.

243
00:16:35.202 --> 00:16:37.955
Your father was unlike
any guy I'd ever seen.

244
00:16:38.038 --> 00:16:40.207
He was just dazzling.

245
00:16:40.290 --> 00:16:42.584
Well, they're always dazzling.

246
00:16:42.668 --> 00:16:44.878
We were really in love, Percy.

247
00:16:45.963 --> 00:16:49.091
And then you came along,
and then it was just perfect.

248
00:16:50.092 --> 00:16:51.719
But he had to leave.

249
00:16:53.345 --> 00:16:55.139
So, he did abandon us.

250
00:16:55.723 --> 00:16:59.226
No, honey, he was forced to.
He loved you.

251
00:16:59.309 --> 00:17:03.731
Leaving you-- it was probably
the most difficult thing he ever did.

252
00:17:09.153 --> 00:17:11.030
(mooing)

253
00:17:14.533 --> 00:17:16.160
Why did he have to go?

254
00:17:17.244 --> 00:17:18.829
Because he's...

255
00:17:18.912 --> 00:17:20.414
-Sally, watch out!
-PERCY: Whoa!

256
00:17:20.497 --> 00:17:22.666
(tires screech)

257
00:17:22.750 --> 00:17:25.044
(screaming)

258
00:17:28.630 --> 00:17:30.174
(groaning)

259
00:17:30.257 --> 00:17:32.843
-Percy.
-Mom, you all right?

260
00:17:32.926 --> 00:17:34.511
-Yeah. Yeah.
-Grover, you all right?

261
00:17:34.595 --> 00:17:36.764
(groaning)

262
00:17:36.847 --> 00:17:38.849
Is it me, or is it raining cows?

263
00:17:38.932 --> 00:17:40.934
(Sally panting)

264
00:17:41.018 --> 00:17:43.645
(rumbling)

265
00:17:43.729 --> 00:17:45.564
What is that?

266
00:17:45.647 --> 00:17:47.149
SALLY: Get out!

267
00:17:47.232 --> 00:17:48.817
Hurry! Come on!

268
00:17:48.901 --> 00:17:50.611
Why are you taking your pants off?

269
00:17:50.694 --> 00:17:52.321
-What are you doing?
-My job.

270
00:17:52.404 --> 00:17:54.698
Whoa! Whoa!
You're half donkey?

271
00:17:54.782 --> 00:17:56.200
I'm half goat.

272
00:17:56.283 --> 00:17:57.367
(grunting)

273
00:18:01.872 --> 00:18:03.540
(grunting)

274
00:18:03.624 --> 00:18:05.542
Guys, watch all this glass.

275
00:18:05.626 --> 00:18:07.169
Come on! Get out the car!

276
00:18:07.252 --> 00:18:09.171
That thing's getting closer!

277
00:18:09.254 --> 00:18:11.924
-You don't even need these.
-Look, man, those are just for show.

278
00:18:12.007 --> 00:18:13.717
-Follow me!
-Whoa!

279
00:18:15.677 --> 00:18:18.472
(grunting)

280
00:18:18.555 --> 00:18:19.807
This way, guys. This way!

281
00:18:19.890 --> 00:18:21.850
Come on! Come on!

282
00:18:21.934 --> 00:18:23.435
Come on! Run!

283
00:18:23.519 --> 00:18:24.645
Run!

284
00:18:24.728 --> 00:18:26.063
(growling)

285
00:18:26.146 --> 00:18:27.314
(panting)

286
00:18:27.397 --> 00:18:29.149
(roaring)

287
00:18:29.233 --> 00:18:30.359
(gasps)

288
00:18:30.442 --> 00:18:33.320
(screaming)

289
00:18:38.575 --> 00:18:40.369
Come on! Come on!

290
00:18:41.453 --> 00:18:43.705
(panting)

291
00:18:45.124 --> 00:18:47.167
We're here! Come on!

292
00:18:53.882 --> 00:18:56.093
(all panting)

293
00:18:56.176 --> 00:18:57.177
-(whooshing)
-(grunting)

294
00:18:57.261 --> 00:18:59.221
Mom, what are you doing?

295
00:18:59.304 --> 00:19:00.722
This is as far as I can go.

296
00:19:00.806 --> 00:19:02.641
-No. Come on!
-I can't go through.

297
00:19:02.724 --> 00:19:04.017
I'm not like you.

298
00:19:04.101 --> 00:19:05.686
Look, I'm not leaving without you.

299
00:19:05.769 --> 00:19:08.438
You have to. You're meant to.

300
00:19:08.522 --> 00:19:09.606
(growling)

301
00:19:09.690 --> 00:19:12.442
(screaming)

302
00:19:12.526 --> 00:19:14.236
(roaring)

303
00:19:14.319 --> 00:19:16.029
(groaning)

304
00:19:16.113 --> 00:19:17.948
Put my mother down!

305
00:19:18.031 --> 00:19:21.451
Percy, go.
You're safe inside the gate.

306
00:19:21.535 --> 00:19:23.120
-What can I do?
-Listen, use the pen!

307
00:19:23.203 --> 00:19:25.372
-What?
-Use Brunner's pen and click it.

308
00:19:26.540 --> 00:19:28.167
Whoa!

309
00:19:28.250 --> 00:19:29.626
(screaming)

310
00:19:29.710 --> 00:19:31.170
(whooshing)

311
00:19:32.671 --> 00:19:34.047
(growling)

312
00:19:36.717 --> 00:19:38.677
(grunting)

313
00:19:42.347 --> 00:19:43.432
(groaning)

314
00:19:45.684 --> 00:19:46.852
(panting)

315
00:19:46.935 --> 00:19:49.146
-(Minotaur roars)
-(Percy gasps)

316
00:19:49.229 --> 00:19:50.898
Perce, are you okay?

317
00:19:50.981 --> 00:19:52.357
(growling, huffing)

318
00:19:56.236 --> 00:19:57.571
(panting)

319
00:19:57.654 --> 00:19:59.281
(growling)

320
00:20:01.241 --> 00:20:02.242
(roaring)

321
00:20:02.326 --> 00:20:04.036
Percy, behind you!

322
00:20:05.370 --> 00:20:07.789
(grunting)

323
00:20:07.873 --> 00:20:09.666
(roaring)

324
00:20:09.750 --> 00:20:10.918
(grunts, sighs)

325
00:20:11.001 --> 00:20:13.754
(howling)

326
00:20:16.340 --> 00:20:18.467
(sighing)

327
00:20:18.550 --> 00:20:20.469
-Perce, you okay?
-I'm not feeling...

328
00:20:20.552 --> 00:20:21.678
Percy!

329
00:20:21.762 --> 00:20:23.805
(groans, gasps)

330
00:20:48.580 --> 00:20:52.167
GROVER:
Perce. I'm sure glad you're alive.

331
00:20:54.795 --> 00:20:56.296
Ow!

332
00:20:56.380 --> 00:20:57.589
Oh.

333
00:21:04.721 --> 00:21:06.890
PERCY: Where am I?
What is this place?

334
00:21:06.974 --> 00:21:08.433
The infirmary.

335
00:21:08.517 --> 00:21:10.519
You've been unconscious
for three days.

336
00:21:10.602 --> 00:21:11.645
Three days?

337
00:21:12.896 --> 00:21:17.109
So, uh, Perce, what do you remember?

338
00:21:17.192 --> 00:21:20.862
(scoffs)
Some... crazy dream.

339
00:21:20.946 --> 00:21:23.115
I don't know. There was... a monster.

340
00:21:23.198 --> 00:21:24.408
My mom was there.

341
00:21:24.491 --> 00:21:27.744
Well, you were there, too,
but you were some weird hybrid...

342
00:21:27.828 --> 00:21:29.955
man-goat thing. Whoa!

343
00:21:32.791 --> 00:21:34.209
Yeah.

344
00:21:34.293 --> 00:21:36.128
The politically correct term is satyr.

345
00:21:37.129 --> 00:21:38.714
No.

346
00:21:38.797 --> 00:21:42.551
No, no, no, no!

347
00:21:42.634 --> 00:21:44.511
All of it was real?

348
00:21:44.594 --> 00:21:46.138
My mom's gone?

349
00:21:47.222 --> 00:21:48.974
I'm sorry, Percy.

350
00:21:49.057 --> 00:21:50.976
I try, man. I really do.

351
00:21:52.811 --> 00:21:54.646
But, frankly,
I'm just a junior protector.

352
00:21:54.730 --> 00:21:56.106
I don't have my horns yet.

353
00:21:57.482 --> 00:21:59.067
It was my fault.

354
00:21:59.151 --> 00:22:01.445
It was my job to protect you.

355
00:22:01.528 --> 00:22:03.363
Both of you.

356
00:22:04.865 --> 00:22:08.452
(heavy sigh)

357
00:22:08.535 --> 00:22:11.038
-(men grunting)
-MAN: Good. Hold your position.

358
00:22:12.080 --> 00:22:13.373
Nice. Up.

359
00:22:13.457 --> 00:22:17.085
So, this is Camp Half Blood.

360
00:22:17.169 --> 00:22:18.587
"Half," meaning what?

361
00:22:18.670 --> 00:22:20.088
I think you know.

362
00:22:20.172 --> 00:22:21.965
"Half" meaning
half mortal, half god.

363
00:22:22.049 --> 00:22:25.552
-MAN: Fire!
-Whoa! Guys, watch the arrows!

364
00:22:25.635 --> 00:22:27.554
Newcomer. Hello.

365
00:22:27.637 --> 00:22:28.930
Gosh!

366
00:22:29.014 --> 00:22:32.809
Look, man, remember all the myths
about Greek gods and goddesses?

367
00:22:32.893 --> 00:22:34.853
Well, they're not myths.

368
00:22:34.936 --> 00:22:37.147
Look, remember what
Mr. Brunner said?

369
00:22:37.230 --> 00:22:39.941
Sometimes they come down to Earth
and they fall in love with mortals,

370
00:22:40.025 --> 00:22:42.527
and then they have... kids?

371
00:22:42.611 --> 00:22:43.737
No way.

372
00:22:43.820 --> 00:22:45.614
Yes way.

373
00:22:45.697 --> 00:22:47.866
Yep, you're a demigod!

374
00:22:47.949 --> 00:22:49.826
Two points for Percy Jackson!

375
00:22:49.910 --> 00:22:51.620
(laughs)

376
00:22:51.703 --> 00:22:53.455
Look, don't worry,
but you're not alone.

377
00:22:53.538 --> 00:22:56.083
There's hundreds in the world.
Some lead normal lives,

378
00:22:56.166 --> 00:22:58.210
and some-- I'm not allowed
to divulge the names--

379
00:22:58.293 --> 00:22:59.836
are very famous.

380
00:22:59.920 --> 00:23:03.006
I'm talking about, like,
White House famous.

381
00:23:03.090 --> 00:23:04.466
See, man, this place right here,

382
00:23:04.549 --> 00:23:07.386
this is the place where you learn
to harness your powers.

383
00:23:07.469 --> 00:23:10.389
You're trained to become
leaders, warriors, and heroes.

384
00:23:10.472 --> 00:23:12.891
PERCY: I think you have
the wrong guy, all right?

385
00:23:12.974 --> 00:23:14.976
I'm not a hero. I'm a loser.

386
00:23:15.060 --> 00:23:17.229
I have dyslexia, ADHD.

387
00:23:17.312 --> 00:23:20.148
GROVER:
And those are your greatest gifts.

388
00:23:20.232 --> 00:23:22.651
When you try to read, the words
float off the page, right?

389
00:23:22.734 --> 00:23:26.029
That's because your brain is hardwired
for ancient Greek, not English.

390
00:23:26.113 --> 00:23:29.032
Like... at the museum, I can read.

391
00:23:29.116 --> 00:23:30.117
Yeah.

392
00:23:30.200 --> 00:23:32.077
And your ADHD...

393
00:23:33.537 --> 00:23:37.040
You're impulsive, Percy.
You can't be still.

394
00:23:37.124 --> 00:23:39.543
Those are your natural
battle reflexes, man.

395
00:23:39.626 --> 00:23:42.087
They kept you alive in your fight.

396
00:23:42.170 --> 00:23:45.882
Look, no pitiful loser
can defeat a Minotaur.

397
00:23:46.967 --> 00:23:48.927
Your blood is special.

398
00:23:49.010 --> 00:23:50.971
It's the blood of a god.

399
00:23:52.055 --> 00:23:53.682
This is a lot to process.

400
00:23:54.182 --> 00:23:56.768
Yeah, a lot, a lot.

401
00:23:57.352 --> 00:24:00.522
(students grunting)

402
00:24:00.605 --> 00:24:02.899
This is where you do most
of your battle training.

403
00:24:02.983 --> 00:24:06.486
(students grunting)

404
00:24:17.289 --> 00:24:19.082
What's her name?

405
00:24:19.166 --> 00:24:21.334
(laughs)

406
00:24:21.418 --> 00:24:23.545
She will squash you like a bug.

407
00:24:23.628 --> 00:24:25.255
Her name.

408
00:24:25.338 --> 00:24:29.634
Annabeth, daughter
of Athena, the goddess of wisdom.

409
00:24:33.930 --> 00:24:35.223
Hey, no staring.

410
00:24:35.307 --> 00:24:37.309
Keep it moving.
Keep it moving. Come on.

411
00:24:37.392 --> 00:24:38.685
PERCY:
Uh-huh.

412
00:24:40.645 --> 00:24:44.274
There's someone I want you to see.
Check this out.

413
00:24:53.158 --> 00:24:55.243
-Oh, wow.
-(chuckles)

414
00:24:58.121 --> 00:25:00.040
What are those things?

415
00:25:00.123 --> 00:25:02.751
They're centaurs.
(laughs)

416
00:25:02.834 --> 00:25:04.878
PERCY:
Wait a minute.

417
00:25:04.961 --> 00:25:06.296
Is that Mr. Brunner?

418
00:25:06.379 --> 00:25:07.547
Come on.

419
00:25:09.216 --> 00:25:11.051
Whoa, w-w-whoa.

420
00:25:11.134 --> 00:25:12.969
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

421
00:25:13.053 --> 00:25:14.763
(chuckles)

422
00:25:14.846 --> 00:25:16.598
Mr. Brunner?

423
00:25:16.681 --> 00:25:19.935
In my world,
I'm known as Chiron.

424
00:25:21.019 --> 00:25:22.270
Are you recovered?

425
00:25:22.354 --> 00:25:23.813
Am <i>I </i>recovered?

426
00:25:23.897 --> 00:25:28.193
You, you're not in a wheelchair.
You have...

427
00:25:28.777 --> 00:25:30.403
A real horse's ass.

428
00:25:31.404 --> 00:25:35.158
I apologize for hiding my true form,
but I needed to keep an eye on you.

429
00:25:35.659 --> 00:25:37.494
I hope you'll forgive me.

430
00:25:37.577 --> 00:25:38.578
Come.

431
00:25:42.707 --> 00:25:44.543
(horse neighs)

432
00:25:50.090 --> 00:25:51.967
(women chatting and laughing)

433
00:25:52.050 --> 00:25:54.678
-Hey, Grover!
-Grover!

434
00:25:54.761 --> 00:25:55.929
(overlapping chatter)

435
00:25:56.012 --> 00:25:59.307
Ooh, the daughters of Aphrodite.

436
00:25:59.391 --> 00:26:00.559
Okay, all right, guys.

437
00:26:00.642 --> 00:26:02.185
You guys got a lot of catching up to do.

438
00:26:02.269 --> 00:26:05.063
Their mother is the goddess of love,
so you know where that leads.

439
00:26:05.146 --> 00:26:07.774
Hey, baby! Whoo!

440
00:26:07.857 --> 00:26:09.234
Hmph! Satyrs.

441
00:26:09.317 --> 00:26:11.236
-(daughters whooping)
-Whoo! (laughs)

442
00:26:12.320 --> 00:26:13.572
PERCY:
What is this place?

443
00:26:15.073 --> 00:26:16.575
Welcome home.

444
00:26:16.658 --> 00:26:20.453
Your father built this... for you.

445
00:26:22.581 --> 00:26:23.623
Wow.

446
00:26:31.673 --> 00:26:33.174
This whole place is mine?

447
00:26:49.149 --> 00:26:51.318
This thing's got some weight to it.

448
00:26:52.902 --> 00:26:54.821
(sighs)

449
00:26:57.824 --> 00:26:59.326
My father is Poseidon.

450
00:26:59.826 --> 00:27:01.703
God of the seas.

451
00:27:02.287 --> 00:27:04.664
Why didn't anybody tell me?

452
00:27:04.748 --> 00:27:06.499
It was for your own safety.

453
00:27:08.001 --> 00:27:12.047
It's exceedingly rare for a child
to be born to one of the Big Three.

454
00:27:15.008 --> 00:27:19.012
You're very powerful... a threat.

455
00:27:19.095 --> 00:27:20.138
A threat?

456
00:27:20.221 --> 00:27:21.723
Who am I threatening?

457
00:27:22.766 --> 00:27:24.643
Poseidon's brothers...

458
00:27:25.644 --> 00:27:27.479
Zeus and Hades.

459
00:27:29.522 --> 00:27:32.275
That's why your mother
married your stepfather.

460
00:27:32.359 --> 00:27:36.696
His pungent odor masked
the smell of your blood

461
00:27:36.780 --> 00:27:40.992
and hid you from anything or anyone

462
00:27:41.076 --> 00:27:42.827
the gods would send to kill you.

463
00:27:44.537 --> 00:27:47.123
My mother put up
with that creep to protect me?

464
00:27:47.207 --> 00:27:48.416
Mm-hmm.

465
00:27:52.212 --> 00:27:53.922
I wish I had known.

466
00:27:54.923 --> 00:27:57.384
She sacrificed so much for me.

467
00:28:00.970 --> 00:28:02.639
Now she's gone.

468
00:28:10.146 --> 00:28:11.606
Why am I even here?

469
00:28:11.690 --> 00:28:14.317
CHIRON: You're here
because you're in jeopardy.

470
00:28:14.401 --> 00:28:16.736
Everyone thinks you're
the lightning thief.

471
00:28:17.320 --> 00:28:18.822
Look, I didn't steal it.

472
00:28:23.326 --> 00:28:27.247
Zeus' bolt is the most
powerful weapon ever created.

473
00:28:28.248 --> 00:28:30.417
And if it's not returned
by the summer solstice

474
00:28:30.500 --> 00:28:32.627
in ten days, there will be a war.

475
00:28:32.711 --> 00:28:34.504
This is your problem,
all right? Not mine.

476
00:28:34.587 --> 00:28:36.631
This is about your world, not mine.

477
00:28:36.715 --> 00:28:38.216
This is about all worlds.

478
00:28:40.385 --> 00:28:41.928
Olympians would be
forced to choose sides.

479
00:28:42.011 --> 00:28:43.930
Earth would become a battleground--

480
00:28:44.013 --> 00:28:47.684
mountains erupted,
earthquakes, raging fires.

481
00:28:47.767 --> 00:28:50.603
The end of life as you know it.

482
00:28:56.776 --> 00:28:58.194
What can we do?

483
00:28:58.278 --> 00:29:00.196
I want to take you to Olympus,

484
00:29:00.280 --> 00:29:02.866
convince Zeus of your innocence.

485
00:29:02.949 --> 00:29:06.202
Someone's using you to start a war.

486
00:29:07.996 --> 00:29:09.539
What are we doing here? Let's go now.

487
00:29:09.622 --> 00:29:14.043
Your boldness is commendable,
but outside those gates,

488
00:29:14.127 --> 00:29:16.880
you will be in danger at all times.

489
00:29:16.963 --> 00:29:21.176
The Fury and the Minotaur
were only the beginning.

490
00:29:21.259 --> 00:29:25.054
First, we must train.

491
00:29:29.809 --> 00:29:33.229
GROVER (laughs):
This is always a fun game to watch.

492
00:29:34.314 --> 00:29:37.317
PERCY: Ow, God, how do you guys
wear this stuff? It weighs more than me.

493
00:29:37.400 --> 00:29:39.235
Look, trust me,
wear it or you'll get killed.

494
00:29:39.319 --> 00:29:41.446
-(chuckles)
-Wait, what, what? Wait...

495
00:29:41.529 --> 00:29:43.281
CHIRON:
Heroes!

496
00:29:43.364 --> 00:29:45.408
Warriors!

497
00:29:45.492 --> 00:29:46.868
Fall in!

498
00:29:53.041 --> 00:29:54.667
Hustle, hustle!

499
00:29:54.751 --> 00:29:57.754
Dylan, Paris, stop lollygagging!

500
00:29:59.839 --> 00:30:02.550
Percy, step forward.

501
00:30:06.721 --> 00:30:10.558
This is Percy Jackson.

502
00:30:10.642 --> 00:30:11.851
(indistinct whispering)

503
00:30:11.935 --> 00:30:14.229
And he's going to need a team.

504
00:30:14.813 --> 00:30:16.064
LUKE: We'll take him.

505
00:30:20.610 --> 00:30:21.945
I'm Luke...

506
00:30:22.028 --> 00:30:26.199
son of Hermes and camp leader--
not necessarily in that order.

507
00:30:26.282 --> 00:30:27.575
Where's your helmet?

508
00:30:28.576 --> 00:30:29.786
No one gave me one.

509
00:30:29.869 --> 00:30:31.162
Uh...

510
00:30:32.247 --> 00:30:34.415
Chiron, you still got your wheelchair?

511
00:30:34.499 --> 00:30:35.792
Kid's going to need it.

512
00:30:35.875 --> 00:30:37.877
You're a goner, man.

513
00:30:39.504 --> 00:30:42.632
I'm messing with you. Smile a little bit.
It's good for you, kid.

514
00:30:42.715 --> 00:30:44.050
Anybody got an extra helmet?

515
00:30:44.133 --> 00:30:46.219
Please pass it up.

516
00:30:48.137 --> 00:30:51.057
Uh... try it on.

517
00:30:52.100 --> 00:30:53.685
That'll protect you.

518
00:30:53.768 --> 00:30:55.144
So will all of us.

519
00:30:55.895 --> 00:30:58.273
Welcome to the Blue Soldiers, my friend.

520
00:30:58.356 --> 00:31:01.693
CHIRON: All right, I want everyone
in position for Capture the Flag.

521
00:31:01.776 --> 00:31:05.822
First team to capture
the enemy's banner wins.

522
00:31:06.406 --> 00:31:07.824
Dismissed.

523
00:31:09.492 --> 00:31:11.077
RED SOLDIER LEADER:
Steady...

524
00:31:11.160 --> 00:31:12.245
Steady!

525
00:31:12.328 --> 00:31:13.329
Now!

526
00:31:13.413 --> 00:31:16.541
(all yelling)

527
00:31:23.298 --> 00:31:25.425
(grunting)

528
00:31:27.552 --> 00:31:29.387
(screams, grunts)

529
00:31:29.470 --> 00:31:32.015
(grunting and yelling)

530
00:31:32.098 --> 00:31:34.559
Percy, I know where the flag's at.
Come on.

531
00:31:34.642 --> 00:31:35.894
(panting)

532
00:31:35.977 --> 00:31:39.564
(grunting and yelling)

533
00:31:39.647 --> 00:31:42.650
Keep your eyes open.
Don't get killed.

534
00:31:42.734 --> 00:31:44.819
W-W-W-Whoa, whoa!

535
00:31:44.903 --> 00:31:46.321
-(soldiers grunting)
-Whoa.

536
00:31:46.404 --> 00:31:47.906
(grunting)

537
00:31:50.450 --> 00:31:51.993
(Percy panting, soldier grunting)

538
00:31:52.076 --> 00:31:53.578
-Whoa!
-(soldier grunts)

539
00:31:53.661 --> 00:31:55.580
(both grunting)

540
00:31:55.663 --> 00:31:56.998
(Percy panting)

541
00:31:57.081 --> 00:31:58.291
I'm coming. Buddy, I'm coming.

542
00:31:58.374 --> 00:32:00.209
Sons of Ares-- watch out, whoa.

543
00:32:00.293 --> 00:32:02.128
-That's a sword. That's a sword.
-(grunting)

544
00:32:03.838 --> 00:32:05.089
(panting)

545
00:32:05.173 --> 00:32:08.051
Oh, you guys take camp
way too seriously.

546
00:32:08.134 --> 00:32:09.510
Go!

547
00:32:09.594 --> 00:32:10.803
(all grunting)

548
00:32:20.271 --> 00:32:21.397
No...

549
00:32:21.481 --> 00:32:22.941
...way!

550
00:32:23.024 --> 00:32:26.819
Percy, get out of here.
Go look for the flag.

551
00:32:26.903 --> 00:32:28.988
How did I just do that?

552
00:32:35.495 --> 00:32:38.498
(panting)

553
00:32:47.465 --> 00:32:49.300
No...

554
00:32:56.516 --> 00:32:58.810
(laughs)

555
00:33:00.228 --> 00:33:01.688
I won.

556
00:33:03.231 --> 00:33:04.232
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

557
00:33:04.315 --> 00:33:06.818
Did you really think
it would be that easy?

558
00:33:11.948 --> 00:33:15.451
My mother is goddess
of wisdom and battle strategy.

559
00:33:15.535 --> 00:33:18.121
Do you know what that means?

560
00:33:18.204 --> 00:33:20.206
I always win.

561
00:33:20.289 --> 00:33:22.583
I always lose.

562
00:33:22.667 --> 00:33:24.210
Maybe we're both wrong.

563
00:33:24.293 --> 00:33:26.170
(Annabeth grunts, Percy gasps)

564
00:33:26.254 --> 00:33:28.548
Aah! Ow!

565
00:33:43.646 --> 00:33:45.440
Okay, Chiron, shouldn't we
get in there and stop 'em?

566
00:33:45.523 --> 00:33:47.525
-She's killing him, man.
-You've got to be kidding.

567
00:33:47.608 --> 00:33:49.318
This is the best part.

568
00:33:49.402 --> 00:33:50.945
(both grunting)

569
00:33:56.284 --> 00:33:58.161
Stand up and fight.

570
00:34:00.163 --> 00:34:01.372
Hero.

571
00:34:03.082 --> 00:34:04.208
(both grunting)

572
00:34:04.292 --> 00:34:06.502
(Annabeth panting)

573
00:34:06.586 --> 00:34:07.754
(Percy grunts)

574
00:34:07.837 --> 00:34:09.714
(Red Soldiers cheering)

575
00:34:16.012 --> 00:34:18.139
Come on, Perce.
Come on, Perce.

576
00:34:18.222 --> 00:34:20.767
(cheering continues)

577
00:34:25.188 --> 00:34:27.231
POSEIDON:
<i>Go to the water.</i>

578
00:34:35.239 --> 00:34:37.575
<i>The water will give you power.</i>

579
00:34:50.296 --> 00:34:53.591
(soft jingling)

580
00:34:59.388 --> 00:35:02.225
(soft jingling)

581
00:35:05.103 --> 00:35:07.980
(soft jingling)

582
00:35:10.274 --> 00:35:12.276
(grunts)

583
00:35:27.667 --> 00:35:29.710
-Take him out.
-Go for it.

584
00:35:32.296 --> 00:35:34.215
(yells)

585
00:35:34.298 --> 00:35:35.633
(grunting)

586
00:35:49.105 --> 00:35:51.607
(Chiron and Grover laughing)

587
00:35:51.691 --> 00:35:52.692
Yeah!

588
00:35:53.693 --> 00:35:55.903
(yelling)

589
00:35:55.987 --> 00:35:57.363
Hya! Hya! Hya!

590
00:35:57.446 --> 00:35:58.990
(Red Soldier grunts)

591
00:36:17.508 --> 00:36:19.385
(both panting)

592
00:36:37.069 --> 00:36:39.030
(blade whooshes)

593
00:36:39.113 --> 00:36:40.740
(quietly)
Huh?

594
00:36:53.753 --> 00:36:56.714
(Blue Soldiers cheering)

595
00:37:03.221 --> 00:37:04.931
Yeah, Perce!

596
00:37:05.014 --> 00:37:08.267
(cheering continues)

597
00:37:11.479 --> 00:37:13.689
(laughter, indistinct chatter)

598
00:37:13.773 --> 00:37:15.691
-Yeah!
-Sons of Ares!

599
00:37:21.072 --> 00:37:23.783
-Sons of Ares!
-Whoo!

600
00:37:23.866 --> 00:37:25.701
-Get up there.
-Yeah!

601
00:37:25.785 --> 00:37:27.578
All right, yeah!

602
00:37:27.662 --> 00:37:29.455
GROVER:
Excuse me, excuse me.

603
00:37:29.538 --> 00:37:31.916
Ladies and gentlemen, the son
of Poseidon is coming through.

604
00:37:31.999 --> 00:37:34.961
A hero is coming through.
Move it.

605
00:37:35.044 --> 00:37:36.629
Hey, no dirty looks.
Stop that.

606
00:37:36.712 --> 00:37:37.713
Sorry.

607
00:37:37.797 --> 00:37:39.215
Um, hey, Percy?

608
00:37:40.049 --> 00:37:41.968
Um, we're having a party
at our place later.

609
00:37:42.051 --> 00:37:43.970
And we would really love it
if you came.

610
00:37:44.053 --> 00:37:45.596
I would love to come;
that'd be great.

611
00:37:45.680 --> 00:37:47.765
-That would be amazing.
-Awesome.

612
00:37:47.848 --> 00:37:49.558
I would love to come, too--
to the party.

613
00:37:49.642 --> 00:37:51.644
You know, thanks
for inviting me, ladies.

614
00:37:51.727 --> 00:37:53.062
Beat it, nymphs.

615
00:37:53.145 --> 00:37:56.482
Wait. Don't leave.
Ladies, I'm available.

616
00:37:56.565 --> 00:37:58.276
Wait, come on, don't leave.
I'm available.

617
00:37:58.359 --> 00:38:00.152
What time is the party?

618
00:38:00.236 --> 00:38:02.738
-Feeling like a hero?
-More like a mutant.

619
00:38:03.322 --> 00:38:06.742
I'm not going to grow a fish tail or gills
or anything like that, am I?

620
00:38:06.826 --> 00:38:08.452
Not likely.

621
00:38:08.536 --> 00:38:10.830
Although a huge ego
isn't out of the question.

622
00:38:14.542 --> 00:38:16.585
You know, you could have
killed me out there?

623
00:38:16.669 --> 00:38:19.088
I could have died if I was normal.

624
00:38:19.171 --> 00:38:20.589
But you aren't.

625
00:38:21.841 --> 00:38:24.552
I get a sense that you
don't like me very much.

626
00:38:24.635 --> 00:38:26.262
It's possible.

627
00:38:26.345 --> 00:38:27.930
I mean, our parents hate each other.

628
00:38:28.139 --> 00:38:31.142
-Wait. They do?
-Mm-hmm.

629
00:38:31.225 --> 00:38:34.645
I definitely have
strong feelings for you.

630
00:38:34.729 --> 00:38:37.773
Just haven't decided
if they're positive or negative yet.

631
00:38:39.317 --> 00:38:42.570
Well, you let me know
when you figure it out.

632
00:38:43.154 --> 00:38:44.572
You'll be the first.

633
00:38:49.577 --> 00:38:50.870
(all gasping, murmuring)

634
00:39:01.297 --> 00:39:04.050
(screaming)

635
00:39:05.968 --> 00:39:08.846
Percy Jackson, show yourself!

636
00:39:13.142 --> 00:39:14.143
(crowd screaming)

637
00:39:16.687 --> 00:39:18.898
(gasping)

638
00:39:27.073 --> 00:39:28.574
(screaming)

639
00:39:28.657 --> 00:39:29.658
CHIRON:
Hades!

640
00:39:29.742 --> 00:39:30.743
Stay back!

641
00:39:33.037 --> 00:39:36.916
Percy Jackson, bring me the bolt.

642
00:39:40.461 --> 00:39:42.338
Be a good boy.

643
00:39:42.421 --> 00:39:46.675
Hand it to me and I will
exchange it for your mother.

644
00:39:46.759 --> 00:39:48.886
CHIRON:
Percy.

645
00:39:48.969 --> 00:39:50.971
Don't listen, Percy!

646
00:39:54.725 --> 00:39:56.519
My mother's gone!

647
00:39:57.770 --> 00:40:01.315
No, your mother is still alive.

648
00:40:01.399 --> 00:40:04.193
I sent the Minotaur to abduct her.

649
00:40:04.276 --> 00:40:07.154
She is here with me
in the underworld.

650
00:40:14.370 --> 00:40:15.913
Mom?

651
00:40:15.996 --> 00:40:17.373
Percy...

652
00:40:24.004 --> 00:40:25.589
What have you done with my mother?

653
00:40:25.673 --> 00:40:27.883
If you ever want to
see your mother again,

654
00:40:27.967 --> 00:40:29.885
you will bring me the bolt.

655
00:40:29.969 --> 00:40:32.930
(all gasping, murmuring)

656
00:40:35.975 --> 00:40:37.893
Chiron, I have to go get her.

657
00:40:37.977 --> 00:40:40.855
Percy...
you don't have the bolt.

658
00:40:40.938 --> 00:40:42.731
Look, I'll tell him the truth.

659
00:40:42.815 --> 00:40:45.734
When he realizes
I'm not the thief, he'll release her.

660
00:40:45.818 --> 00:40:48.612
No, you cannot
negotiate with Hades.

661
00:40:48.696 --> 00:40:51.907
When he finds out
you don't have the bolt,

662
00:40:51.991 --> 00:40:53.492
he will kill you and your mother.

663
00:40:53.576 --> 00:40:55.744
This is her only chance.

664
00:40:55.828 --> 00:40:58.581
No. Stick to our plan.

665
00:40:59.665 --> 00:41:02.960
Travel to Olympus, bargain with Zeus.

666
00:41:03.043 --> 00:41:06.297
Once you convince him of your
innocence, we will do everything

667
00:41:06.380 --> 00:41:08.382
in our power to bring
back your mother.

668
00:41:11.260 --> 00:41:13.762
-Okay.
-Yes.

669
00:41:20.936 --> 00:41:22.104
(groans)

670
00:41:29.778 --> 00:41:31.113
Going somewhere?

671
00:41:32.114 --> 00:41:34.408
Yeah, yeah.
I'm going... for a walk.

672
00:41:34.492 --> 00:41:35.826
Oh, for a walk!
I'm coming with you.

673
00:41:35.910 --> 00:41:37.244
-No. No.
-Yeah.

674
00:41:37.328 --> 00:41:38.996
-I'm going alone.
-No, I'm coming with you.

675
00:41:39.079 --> 00:41:41.165
-No!
-(laughs) You're being followed.

676
00:41:45.044 --> 00:41:46.962
-GROVER: You're stressing me out.
-Leave me alone.

677
00:41:47.046 --> 00:41:49.215
-We've got a 1:00 demigod curfew, okay?
-Leave me alone.

678
00:41:49.298 --> 00:41:50.674
Go to sleep or something.

679
00:41:50.758 --> 00:41:52.301
No.

680
00:41:52.384 --> 00:41:54.929
ANNABETH: One small victory,
and you're ready to fight Hades?

681
00:41:55.012 --> 00:41:57.139
-Ooh, double team.
-Really? You, too?

682
00:41:57.223 --> 00:42:00.267
Look, I just found out
my mother is still alive.

683
00:42:00.351 --> 00:42:02.353
-I'm going to get her back.
-From the underworld?

684
00:42:02.436 --> 00:42:03.729
Whatever it takes.

685
00:42:03.812 --> 00:42:05.231
Oh, yeah, well, maybe
you'll outsmart Hades.

686
00:42:05.314 --> 00:42:06.315
Maybe I will.

687
00:42:06.398 --> 00:42:07.858
Look, man, I can't let you
do this, okay?

688
00:42:07.942 --> 00:42:11.111
Look, I'm not asking
for your permission.

689
00:42:11.195 --> 00:42:12.238
Okay.

690
00:42:12.321 --> 00:42:16.116
Well, according to regulations,
if I can't stop you, I must accompany you,

691
00:42:16.200 --> 00:42:18.869
'cause I'm your best friend
and your protector.

692
00:42:18.953 --> 00:42:19.995
Junior protector.

693
00:42:20.079 --> 00:42:22.581
(laughs)
Is that really necessary?

694
00:42:22.665 --> 00:42:24.458
I don't need your help, okay?

695
00:42:24.542 --> 00:42:26.585
This is something I have to do on my own.

696
00:42:26.669 --> 00:42:28.254
Yeah, well, we weren't asking
for your permission.

697
00:42:28.337 --> 00:42:29.630
Come on, all right?

698
00:42:29.713 --> 00:42:32.675
Today, you tried to kill me.
Now you want to defend me?

699
00:42:32.758 --> 00:42:35.177
ANNABETH: That wasn't real.
That was just training.

700
00:42:35.261 --> 00:42:36.262
Yeah.

701
00:42:36.345 --> 00:42:39.098
Percy, that's all I've ever done
is train and train and train.

702
00:42:39.181 --> 00:42:43.018
I've grown up here. I've only been
in the outside world a couple of times.

703
00:42:43.102 --> 00:42:46.188
And I've never had the chance
to go on an actual quest.

704
00:42:46.272 --> 00:42:50.985
Besides... you've won one battle,
and I've won hundreds.

705
00:42:51.068 --> 00:42:52.903
You're going to need my experience.

706
00:42:52.987 --> 00:42:54.697
Good point.
(chuckles)

707
00:42:56.240 --> 00:42:58.325
You two really want to come?

708
00:42:58.409 --> 00:42:59.285
-Yeah!
-Yes!

709
00:43:00.661 --> 00:43:03.205
Okay. I guess we're all going.

710
00:43:03.289 --> 00:43:07.167
So, who knows how to
get to the underworld?

711
00:43:07.251 --> 00:43:09.378
Did not think of that one.

712
00:43:11.297 --> 00:43:14.300
I think I know someone who might.

713
00:43:14.383 --> 00:43:16.302
MAN IN VIDEO GAME:
Friendly Harriers inbound.

714
00:43:20.014 --> 00:43:21.599
-Luke?
-Hmm?

715
00:43:23.767 --> 00:43:24.935
Hey, guys.

716
00:43:25.936 --> 00:43:29.523
Percy, figured you'd
stop by sooner or later.

717
00:43:29.607 --> 00:43:31.358
Everybody does.

718
00:43:31.442 --> 00:43:33.444
-(video game gunfire)
-Get away from all that...

719
00:43:33.527 --> 00:43:36.780
Renaissance Faire stuff
out there, you know?

720
00:43:38.157 --> 00:43:40.659
But, uh...

721
00:43:41.243 --> 00:43:43.454
welcome to the modern world.

722
00:43:43.537 --> 00:43:45.623
Cool... new stuff.

723
00:43:48.542 --> 00:43:50.628
What are you guys up to?

724
00:43:50.711 --> 00:43:52.630
We're going to get my mom back.

725
00:43:53.631 --> 00:43:54.757
Oh.

726
00:43:54.840 --> 00:43:56.508
ANNABETH: Your dad
is the messenger of the gods,

727
00:43:56.592 --> 00:44:00.721
one of the only ones who's gotten
in and out of the underworld.

728
00:44:00.804 --> 00:44:02.931
Do you have any idea how?

729
00:44:03.015 --> 00:44:06.560
Mmm... My dad's a jerk.
I've never met him.

730
00:44:07.144 --> 00:44:08.270
You, too?

731
00:44:08.354 --> 00:44:10.481
Guess we all got daddy issues, huh?

732
00:44:10.564 --> 00:44:12.900
That's because all gods
are the same:

733
00:44:12.983 --> 00:44:14.401
selfish.

734
00:44:14.485 --> 00:44:16.528
They only care about themselves.

735
00:44:17.946 --> 00:44:19.948
But I once broke into my dad's house.

736
00:44:20.032 --> 00:44:21.784
Got some cool stuff.

737
00:44:28.999 --> 00:44:30.751
(blows)

738
00:44:30.834 --> 00:44:32.586
(coughs)

739
00:44:34.296 --> 00:44:35.381
For you.

740
00:44:44.556 --> 00:44:45.683
Oh!

741
00:44:46.684 --> 00:44:48.686
Flying shoes?!

742
00:44:48.769 --> 00:44:50.354
Mm-hmm.

743
00:44:50.437 --> 00:44:52.064
They're my dad's.

744
00:44:53.065 --> 00:44:55.067
He has hundreds of these little guys.

745
00:44:55.150 --> 00:44:57.027
(grunts)

746
00:44:58.278 --> 00:45:00.239
Won't even miss 'em.

747
00:45:00.322 --> 00:45:02.032
Look underneath the other one.

748
00:45:07.121 --> 00:45:09.164
You see, people have gone
to the underworld before,

749
00:45:09.248 --> 00:45:10.833
without having to be dead.

750
00:45:10.916 --> 00:45:12.418
Hercules did it. Orpheus did it.

751
00:45:12.501 --> 00:45:14.378
My dad does it all the time.

752
00:45:14.461 --> 00:45:16.171
Getting in's the easy part.

753
00:45:16.255 --> 00:45:19.216
Getting out-- now, that's tricky.

754
00:45:19.299 --> 00:45:21.885
This is a map to Persephone's pearls.

755
00:45:21.969 --> 00:45:25.013
Persephone?
You mean Hades' wife?

756
00:45:25.097 --> 00:45:28.392
Yeah, he forced her to marry him.
Keeps her prisoner.

757
00:45:28.475 --> 00:45:30.352
LUKE: Needless to say,
she hates it there.

758
00:45:30.436 --> 00:45:32.688
It's hot. He's a weirdo.

759
00:45:32.771 --> 00:45:36.275
So, she has, um... secret visitors.

760
00:45:36.358 --> 00:45:38.193
-Mmm.
-Mmm.

761
00:45:38.277 --> 00:45:40.654
LUKE: She keeps pearls hidden
for them all over the world,

762
00:45:40.738 --> 00:45:44.450
and these pearls, they provide
a quick escape from the underworld.

763
00:45:44.533 --> 00:45:46.160
You could use them to get out.

764
00:45:46.243 --> 00:45:48.203
So, how do the pearls work?

765
00:45:48.287 --> 00:45:50.038
Easy.

766
00:45:50.122 --> 00:45:52.458
You take a pearl, step on it,
you crush it,

767
00:45:52.541 --> 00:45:54.543
visualize where you want
to be taken.

768
00:45:54.626 --> 00:45:57.045
Right now, there's three pearls
in the United States.

769
00:45:57.129 --> 00:45:58.338
This map will guide you there.

770
00:45:58.422 --> 00:46:00.966
Right here is your first location.

771
00:46:03.051 --> 00:46:05.679
GROVER: "Auntie Em's
Garden Emporium." Huh.

772
00:46:05.763 --> 00:46:07.931
Once you find the first pearl,
the map will show you

773
00:46:08.015 --> 00:46:11.185
the next one and the next one,
and then you're off to Hades.

774
00:46:11.268 --> 00:46:13.061
Which, um...

775
00:46:14.062 --> 00:46:15.939
reminds me-- you guys...

776
00:46:16.023 --> 00:46:18.442
might need some extra
protection, so, uh...

777
00:46:21.487 --> 00:46:23.489
My favorite shield.

778
00:46:23.572 --> 00:46:25.616
You might want to take a step back.

779
00:46:29.328 --> 00:46:30.454
(clicks)

780
00:46:31.455 --> 00:46:32.539
(gasps)

781
00:46:32.623 --> 00:46:33.916
Mmm.

782
00:46:35.334 --> 00:46:37.252
Hey. Thanks, Luke.

783
00:46:37.336 --> 00:46:39.129
Ah, don't mention it.

784
00:46:39.213 --> 00:46:42.925
But, uh, you're going to have
to promise me one thing.

785
00:46:43.509 --> 00:46:45.511
If you see my dad
on the highway to hell...

786
00:46:45.594 --> 00:46:46.720
Yeah?

787
00:46:46.804 --> 00:46:48.680
...kick his ass for me.

788
00:46:50.015 --> 00:46:54.686
AC/DC:
<i>♪ I'm on the highway to hell ♪</i>

789
00:46:54.770 --> 00:46:58.398
<i>♪ Highway to hell ♪</i>

790
00:46:58.482 --> 00:47:03.111
<i>♪ I'm on the highway to hell ♪</i>

791
00:47:03.195 --> 00:47:06.365
<i>♪ Highway to hell ♪</i>

792
00:47:06.448 --> 00:47:09.451
<i>♪ Mmm ♪</i>

793
00:47:09.535 --> 00:47:11.537
<i>♪ Don't stop me ♪</i>

794
00:47:13.831 --> 00:47:15.290
<i>♪ Hey, hey ♪</i>

795
00:47:15.374 --> 00:47:19.127
<i>(guitar solo plays)</i>

796
00:47:19.211 --> 00:47:22.339
This place definitely
needs an extreme makeover.

797
00:47:22.422 --> 00:47:24.508
<i>(music fades out)</i>

798
00:47:27.094 --> 00:47:28.512
Hello!

799
00:47:30.389 --> 00:47:31.723
Hello?

800
00:47:31.807 --> 00:47:33.642
Anybody home in Auntie-ville?

801
00:47:33.725 --> 00:47:35.310
(chuckles)
Check this out.

802
00:47:35.394 --> 00:47:36.979
They got free sodas.

803
00:47:37.062 --> 00:47:38.814
(chuckling)

804
00:47:38.897 --> 00:47:39.940
(squeaking)

805
00:47:40.023 --> 00:47:41.567
(shrieks)

806
00:47:41.650 --> 00:47:43.819
Okay. That's nasty.

807
00:47:43.902 --> 00:47:46.572
The health department needs
to give this place a F.

808
00:47:46.655 --> 00:47:48.532
Ooh...

809
00:47:50.409 --> 00:47:52.744
Hey, guys, check this out.

810
00:47:55.414 --> 00:47:57.416
(jingling)

811
00:48:01.712 --> 00:48:02.963
Look at this.

812
00:48:05.048 --> 00:48:06.258
Nice.

813
00:48:07.259 --> 00:48:09.177
Gold drachmas.

814
00:48:09.261 --> 00:48:10.721
That means we're on the right track.

815
00:48:11.305 --> 00:48:12.514
Here.

816
00:48:14.308 --> 00:48:15.767
How are we going
to find a pearl in this place?

817
00:48:15.851 --> 00:48:17.895
GROVER:
That's a good question.

818
00:48:17.978 --> 00:48:20.272
Okay, let's split up.
Check everything.

819
00:48:20.355 --> 00:48:21.356
-Good idea.
-Yeah.

820
00:48:21.440 --> 00:48:22.524
I'm gonna go this way.

821
00:48:27.446 --> 00:48:28.697
Hello!

822
00:48:45.464 --> 00:48:48.383
-Get out! She's coming!
-What? Who?

823
00:48:48.467 --> 00:48:51.303
We stopped-- d-directions.
My poor husband!

824
00:48:51.386 --> 00:48:54.181
Help me!
Please, help me!

825
00:48:59.478 --> 00:49:01.897
(laughing)

826
00:49:01.980 --> 00:49:03.690
Oh!

827
00:49:03.774 --> 00:49:05.400
Check this out.

828
00:49:05.484 --> 00:49:07.402
He's just like my Uncle Ferdinand.

829
00:49:07.486 --> 00:49:09.404
(laughing)

830
00:49:09.488 --> 00:49:10.697
That's crazy.

831
00:49:11.990 --> 00:49:13.742
Got the mole in the same place.

832
00:49:15.410 --> 00:49:17.996
No. It's not my Uncle Ferdinand,

833
00:49:18.080 --> 00:49:19.957
'cause my Uncle Ferdinand
was killed by...

834
00:49:20.958 --> 00:49:22.501
(whispering) Medusa.

835
00:49:22.584 --> 00:49:24.461
Oh.

836
00:49:24.544 --> 00:49:25.796
Percy!

837
00:49:25.879 --> 00:49:28.423
Annabeth! We're in trouble!

838
00:49:28.507 --> 00:49:29.883
Grover?!

839
00:49:33.679 --> 00:49:36.139
Please, we have to leave
before she finds us!

840
00:49:36.223 --> 00:49:38.558
-Who?
-She turned my husband to stone!

841
00:49:38.642 --> 00:49:40.686
Grover, where are you?

842
00:49:41.979 --> 00:49:43.063
Percy!

843
00:49:43.689 --> 00:49:44.982
Annabeth!

844
00:49:46.066 --> 00:49:47.484
Annabeth, where are you?

845
00:49:47.567 --> 00:49:48.860
Grover!

846
00:49:48.944 --> 00:49:49.987
(grunting)

847
00:49:52.197 --> 00:49:54.366
Come on, man.
Watch where you're going.

848
00:49:54.449 --> 00:49:56.535
-Perce, listen!
-Where are we?

849
00:49:56.618 --> 00:49:58.453
We're in Medusa's lair.

850
00:49:58.537 --> 00:50:00.372
-Annabeth!
-Annie!

851
00:50:00.455 --> 00:50:03.583
We're lost!
We'll never leave!

852
00:50:03.667 --> 00:50:04.751
Don't move.

853
00:50:08.797 --> 00:50:12.634
Well, this is a fabulous surprise.

854
00:50:12.718 --> 00:50:14.386
It's so...

855
00:50:14.970 --> 00:50:18.765
heartening
to have such young visitors.

856
00:50:18.849 --> 00:50:21.393
We get so lonely here.

857
00:50:22.394 --> 00:50:23.687
Don't we?

858
00:50:23.770 --> 00:50:25.147
(hissing)

859
00:50:25.230 --> 00:50:28.900
That's why I create my statues.

860
00:50:31.528 --> 00:50:33.405
They're my only company...

861
00:50:35.782 --> 00:50:37.701
...daughter of Athena.

862
00:50:37.784 --> 00:50:39.244
How do you know me?

863
00:50:39.327 --> 00:50:43.040
You have such beautiful hair.

864
00:50:44.708 --> 00:50:47.586
I once had hair like that.

865
00:50:48.587 --> 00:50:50.922
I was courted...

866
00:50:52.007 --> 00:50:55.385
desired by many suitors.

867
00:50:56.386 --> 00:50:58.805
But that all changed...

868
00:51:00.140 --> 00:51:02.517
because of your mother--

869
00:51:02.601 --> 00:51:05.270
the woman who cursed me.

870
00:51:06.271 --> 00:51:08.440
Who turned me...

871
00:51:10.859 --> 00:51:11.943
Don't look!

872
00:51:12.027 --> 00:51:13.695
...into this!

873
00:51:13.779 --> 00:51:15.322
(hissing)

874
00:51:16.156 --> 00:51:19.785
They say the eyes
are windows to the soul.

875
00:51:20.619 --> 00:51:24.539
I hope you find my eyes...

876
00:51:24.623 --> 00:51:27.250
(snakes hissing and rattling)

877
00:51:27.334 --> 00:51:29.252
...attractive.

878
00:51:31.254 --> 00:51:35.926
So rude, not looking people in the eyes.

879
00:51:36.009 --> 00:51:37.469
(anxious gasping)

880
00:51:37.552 --> 00:51:39.763
Come on...

881
00:51:39.846 --> 00:51:43.850
sneak a peek.

882
00:51:50.649 --> 00:51:53.527
(hissing)

883
00:52:02.661 --> 00:52:05.580
Okay, now, how are we supposed
to fight something we can't look at?

884
00:52:05.664 --> 00:52:07.582
We can look at a reflection.

885
00:52:08.667 --> 00:52:10.210
Check this out.

886
00:52:10.293 --> 00:52:13.004
All right. Good idea.
I'm gonna go get Annabeth.

887
00:52:13.088 --> 00:52:14.381
Okay. I'm going
to take care of Medusa.

888
00:52:14.464 --> 00:52:15.590
All right.

889
00:52:15.674 --> 00:52:17.509
MEDUSA: You make
a wonderful addition

890
00:52:17.592 --> 00:52:19.970
to my collection.

891
00:52:20.053 --> 00:52:23.390
We'll be friends forever.

892
00:52:23.473 --> 00:52:25.100
Do you mind?

893
00:52:28.645 --> 00:52:30.147
Oh, no, no...

894
00:52:30.230 --> 00:52:32.065
(snakes hissing, rattling)

895
00:52:34.359 --> 00:52:36.611
Sooner or later,

896
00:52:36.695 --> 00:52:40.699
you will open those eyes.

897
00:52:42.325 --> 00:52:48.123
The temptation to look at me
is too hard to resist.

898
00:52:48.206 --> 00:52:50.500
Don't look, Annabeth.
Don't open your eyes.

899
00:52:50.584 --> 00:52:51.877
(hissing)

900
00:52:51.960 --> 00:52:53.712
Who's that?

901
00:52:54.713 --> 00:52:56.923
Another demigod.

902
00:53:03.638 --> 00:53:04.639
Mmm...

903
00:53:05.724 --> 00:53:08.101
I can sense you.

904
00:53:10.687 --> 00:53:12.022
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

905
00:53:13.356 --> 00:53:15.192
(snakes hissing)

906
00:53:16.902 --> 00:53:18.737
(panting)

907
00:53:26.077 --> 00:53:28.413
Hmm...

908
00:53:28.496 --> 00:53:30.665
son of Poseidon.

909
00:53:32.292 --> 00:53:35.462
I used to date your daddy.

910
00:53:35.545 --> 00:53:36.546
(grunts)

911
00:53:40.008 --> 00:53:42.302
(gasps, groans)

912
00:53:44.054 --> 00:53:45.889
(hissing in distance)

913
00:53:45.972 --> 00:53:47.682
(gasps, yelps)

914
00:53:47.766 --> 00:53:48.808
Need a hand?

915
00:53:48.892 --> 00:53:50.602
Oh, Grover.

916
00:53:51.937 --> 00:53:53.897
-(Grover grunts)
-Thanks.

917
00:53:53.980 --> 00:53:56.399
-Come on. Let's go.
-Okay.

918
00:53:56.483 --> 00:53:58.443
(grunting)

919
00:54:03.365 --> 00:54:06.701
I hear you have the lightning bolt.

920
00:54:06.785 --> 00:54:08.745
May I see it?

921
00:54:09.329 --> 00:54:11.248
I don't have it!

922
00:54:11.331 --> 00:54:12.832
(hissing)

923
00:54:13.833 --> 00:54:16.670
Let me see your eyes.

924
00:54:16.753 --> 00:54:21.299
I hear they're bluer
than the Circassian Sea.

925
00:54:21.883 --> 00:54:23.718
Open them,

926
00:54:23.802 --> 00:54:26.054
or my hungry babies

927
00:54:26.137 --> 00:54:29.474
will have to open them for you.

928
00:54:31.935 --> 00:54:35.355
But it would be such a pity

929
00:54:35.438 --> 00:54:41.111
to destroy such a young
and handsome face.

930
00:54:42.988 --> 00:54:46.116
Stay with me, Percy.

931
00:54:46.700 --> 00:54:50.036
All you have to do

932
00:54:50.120 --> 00:54:54.457
is look.

933
00:54:58.003 --> 00:55:00.046
(engine revving, tires screeching)

934
00:55:08.471 --> 00:55:09.639
(panting)

935
00:55:09.723 --> 00:55:11.016
Are you okay?

936
00:55:11.099 --> 00:55:13.768
(yells, laughs)

937
00:55:13.852 --> 00:55:15.520
Yeah, I'm okay!

938
00:55:16.855 --> 00:55:18.857
(snakes hissing)

939
00:55:21.943 --> 00:55:24.821
Son of Poseidon!

940
00:55:35.248 --> 00:55:36.374
(gasps)

941
00:55:36.458 --> 00:55:38.585
(panting)

942
00:55:38.668 --> 00:55:40.503
Heads up.

943
00:55:44.299 --> 00:55:46.134
PERCY:
Hey, guys.

944
00:55:46.217 --> 00:55:48.803
It's cool to open up your eyes.

945
00:55:48.887 --> 00:55:53.808
Annabeth, that was great,
great demigod driving.

946
00:55:53.892 --> 00:55:54.934
Thanks.

947
00:55:55.018 --> 00:55:56.102
Oh...

948
00:55:56.186 --> 00:55:57.645
Ugh!

949
00:55:57.729 --> 00:55:59.814
ANNABETH:
We should take it with us.

950
00:55:59.898 --> 00:56:02.025
GROVER:
The head? Oh, no. That's sick.

951
00:56:02.108 --> 00:56:05.612
If you open the eyes,
they still work, dead or alive.

952
00:56:05.695 --> 00:56:08.114
You never know when something
like that might come in handy.

953
00:56:08.198 --> 00:56:09.783
Yeah, you're right,
but I'm not touching it.

954
00:56:09.866 --> 00:56:11.368
Come on, man.
Just take off your jacket.

955
00:56:11.451 --> 00:56:13.078
We'll wrap it up
until we get some ice.

956
00:56:14.162 --> 00:56:16.289
Oh, why I gotta
take off my jacket?

957
00:56:16.373 --> 00:56:17.624
Because you're the protector.

958
00:56:18.666 --> 00:56:20.877
Yeah, you're right.
I am the protector.

959
00:56:20.960 --> 00:56:24.506
So I'm gonna give you my hoodie,
not my jacket, okay?

960
00:56:24.589 --> 00:56:26.716
Come on, you baby.

961
00:56:29.552 --> 00:56:30.845
Disgusting.

962
00:56:30.929 --> 00:56:31.971
Just toss it up.

963
00:56:32.055 --> 00:56:33.848
You know, don't... Ugh!

964
00:56:33.932 --> 00:56:36.226
-Hey. Hey.
-Nasty.

965
00:56:36.309 --> 00:56:37.811
Guys, wait.

966
00:56:38.895 --> 00:56:40.271
The pearl.

967
00:56:45.026 --> 00:56:47.112
One down, two to go.

968
00:56:49.572 --> 00:56:52.951
ANNABETH: Would have been nice
if Luke had warned us about Medusa.

969
00:56:53.034 --> 00:56:54.494
Maybe he just didn't know.

970
00:56:55.495 --> 00:56:57.914
GPS from the gods, where to next?

971
00:56:59.207 --> 00:57:00.291
Let's see.

972
00:57:06.381 --> 00:57:08.341
The Parthenon in Nashville.

973
00:57:08.425 --> 00:57:10.885
Nashville?! Aw, great.

974
00:57:10.969 --> 00:57:12.929
Home of my least favorite music.

975
00:57:13.012 --> 00:57:14.931
Yee-haw!

976
00:57:15.014 --> 00:57:17.809
("I'll Pretend" by Dwight Yoakam playing)

977
00:57:20.145 --> 00:57:22.439
(over radio)
♪ I'll make believe ♪

978
00:57:22.522 --> 00:57:26.317
♪ That the sight of her
in my head's seldom seen ♪

979
00:57:26.401 --> 00:57:28.278
(horn blaring)

980
00:57:28.361 --> 00:57:30.321
-Whoa!
-Whoa! Whoa!

981
00:57:30.405 --> 00:57:31.739
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

982
00:57:31.823 --> 00:57:33.366
-(tires screeching)
-PERCY: Whoa! Move!

983
00:57:33.450 --> 00:57:35.535
(screaming)

984
00:57:35.618 --> 00:57:36.953
Let's stop for the night.

985
00:57:37.036 --> 00:57:38.496
-Let's stop for the night.
-Yeah. Yeah.

986
00:57:38.580 --> 00:57:41.249
-Good idea.
-Oh, my god.

987
00:57:41.332 --> 00:57:46.129
♪ Till there's no need,
I'll make believe... ♪

988
00:57:46.212 --> 00:57:48.298
(song fades out)

989
00:57:59.476 --> 00:58:01.144
Percy.

990
00:58:03.229 --> 00:58:05.356
(whooshing)

991
00:58:18.286 --> 00:58:19.412
Hey.

992
00:58:23.958 --> 00:58:24.959
Hi.

993
00:58:25.043 --> 00:58:26.419
Nice work today.

994
00:58:26.503 --> 00:58:28.463
Thanks.

995
00:58:30.507 --> 00:58:32.133
What happened to you?

996
00:58:32.217 --> 00:58:33.843
Oh...

997
00:58:33.927 --> 00:58:36.596
That poor lady who turned
to stone-- she, um...

998
00:58:36.679 --> 00:58:39.015
she had a tight grip.

999
00:58:41.309 --> 00:58:42.644
Check this out.

1000
00:58:54.906 --> 00:58:57.116
(chuckles)
Cool.

1001
00:58:57.200 --> 00:58:59.244
Very cool.

1002
00:59:01.538 --> 00:59:03.248
So...

1003
00:59:03.331 --> 00:59:05.500
why do our parents hate each other?

1004
00:59:05.583 --> 00:59:09.128
They both wanted to be
patron god of Athens,

1005
00:59:09.212 --> 00:59:12.173
and the people chose Athena.

1006
00:59:12.257 --> 00:59:16.177
And, um, our parents have
hated each other ever since.

1007
00:59:17.178 --> 00:59:19.764
-What's your mom like?
-I don't know.

1008
00:59:20.348 --> 00:59:21.516
I never met her.

1009
00:59:21.599 --> 00:59:22.976
What?

1010
00:59:23.059 --> 00:59:26.020
Wait, is it... is it
like this for everybody?

1011
00:59:26.104 --> 00:59:28.022
Don't any gods see their kids?

1012
00:59:28.106 --> 00:59:29.482
It's forbidden.

1013
00:59:30.817 --> 00:59:33.152
Right after we were born,
Zeus decreed

1014
00:59:33.236 --> 00:59:35.488
that the gods couldn't
have physical contact

1015
00:59:35.572 --> 00:59:37.282
with their mortal offspring.

1016
00:59:37.365 --> 00:59:39.701
Oh, that's a stupid law.

1017
00:59:39.784 --> 00:59:41.035
I agree.

1018
00:59:42.370 --> 00:59:45.039
Although, um...

1019
00:59:45.123 --> 00:59:46.708
between us...

1020
00:59:47.792 --> 00:59:50.670
I think my mother speaks
to me sometimes.

1021
00:59:50.753 --> 00:59:52.547
In times of trouble,

1022
00:59:52.630 --> 00:59:55.633
I hear her voice giving me advice.

1023
00:59:55.717 --> 00:59:57.760
-That's happened to me.
-Yeah.

1024
00:59:57.844 --> 01:00:00.263
That's your father talking to you.

1025
01:00:01.389 --> 01:00:02.890
GROVER:
Hey, yo, Percy!

1026
01:00:02.974 --> 01:00:04.809
Get in here, man.
This is ugly.

1027
01:00:04.892 --> 01:00:06.769
(sighs)

1028
01:00:06.853 --> 01:00:08.313
Right.

1029
01:00:08.396 --> 01:00:10.481
GROVER:
Hey, hurry up!

1030
01:00:10.565 --> 01:00:13.526
Perce, check this out, man.

1031
01:00:13.610 --> 01:00:14.944
You're on TV.

1032
01:00:15.028 --> 01:00:17.447
...surrounding the missing boy,
Percy Jackson,

1033
01:00:17.530 --> 01:00:19.490
and his mother, Sally Ugliano.

1034
01:00:19.574 --> 01:00:22.994
But their relatives have
some interesting theories.

1035
01:00:23.077 --> 01:00:25.872
So, Mr. Ugliano, talk to me
about your son, Percy Jackson.

1036
01:00:25.955 --> 01:00:28.082
No, he's not my son.
He's stepson.

1037
01:00:28.166 --> 01:00:30.209
He did not come from these loins.

1038
01:00:30.293 --> 01:00:31.711
Ever since he started with the drugs

1039
01:00:31.794 --> 01:00:33.379
and the alcohol,
he's never been the same.

1040
01:00:33.463 --> 01:00:35.131
-Oh, no.
-GABE: Five nights ago...

1041
01:00:35.214 --> 01:00:37.634
he tried to kill me, and he
threw his mother on the ground,

1042
01:00:37.717 --> 01:00:39.969
and his cripple friend
then attacked me

1043
01:00:40.053 --> 01:00:42.388
from behind and knocked me out.

1044
01:00:42.472 --> 01:00:46.643
When I woke up, Sally was gone.
She was kidnapped by Percy.

1045
01:00:46.726 --> 01:00:48.102
-She would never leave without...
-Oh, shut up, Gabe.

1046
01:00:48.186 --> 01:00:49.854
-(TV turns off)
-Great.

1047
01:00:49.937 --> 01:00:51.356
Now I'm a fugitive.

1048
01:00:51.439 --> 01:00:53.691
See? That's what I'm
talking about, man.

1049
01:00:53.775 --> 01:00:55.693
Gabe's always running his mouth.

1050
01:00:55.777 --> 01:00:58.655
He's just mad because
I busted him up with my crutches.

1051
01:00:58.738 --> 01:01:00.114
Oh!

1052
01:01:00.198 --> 01:01:01.532
Guys...

1053
01:01:02.867 --> 01:01:05.662
I can't pee with her watching me.

