-Ooh, thanks.

1307
01:15:34.321 --> 01:15:36.281
Thank you. Thanks.

1308
01:15:36.365 --> 01:15:38.116
♪ P-P-Poker face... ♪

1309
01:15:38.200 --> 01:15:41.870
POSEIDON:
<i>No, Percy, don't eat the flower.</i>

1310
01:15:41.954 --> 01:15:47.793
<i>It dulls the senses;</i>
<i>keeps you prisoner here.</i>

1311
01:15:47.876 --> 01:15:50.337
Hey, I think I'm gonna
go get some air. I'll be right back.

1312
01:15:53.423 --> 01:15:55.467
("Mama Told Me Not to Come"
by Three Dog Night playing)

1313
01:15:55.551 --> 01:15:57.010
Another lotus flower?

1314
01:15:57.094 --> 01:15:59.012
No, I'm good. Thank you.

1315
01:15:59.096 --> 01:16:00.722
♪ Sugar in your tea? ♪

1316
01:16:00.806 --> 01:16:02.349
♪ What's all these crazy questions...? ♪

1317
01:16:02.432 --> 01:16:06.061
POSEIDON: <i>Look around you.</i>
<i>Focus. Focus.</i>

1318
01:16:06.144 --> 01:16:08.105
-Another lotus flower?
-Oh, no, thank you.

1319
01:16:10.148 --> 01:16:12.317
-Would you like another one?
-I'm fine.

1320
01:16:12.401 --> 01:16:14.945
♪ Mama told me not to come ♪

1321
01:16:16.405 --> 01:16:18.991
♪ Mama told me not to come... ♪

1322
01:16:19.074 --> 01:16:21.076
PERCY:
<i>The French Connection, </i>huh?

1323
01:16:21.159 --> 01:16:23.453
PINBALL PLAYER:
Yeah. You seen it yet?

1324
01:16:23.537 --> 01:16:27.040
Yeah, yeah, I think so, on DVD.

1325
01:16:27.124 --> 01:16:28.417
What's DVD?

1326
01:16:30.127 --> 01:16:31.378
Seriously?

1327
01:16:32.379 --> 01:16:34.881
Whatever-- I think it's
the best movie of the year.

1328
01:16:34.965 --> 01:16:35.966
What?

1329
01:16:36.049 --> 01:16:37.968
Wait, this year.

1330
01:16:39.052 --> 01:16:41.972
Yeah, this year-- 1971.

1331
01:16:44.933 --> 01:16:47.561
♪ Radio is blastin',
someone's knockin' at the door... ♪

1332
01:16:47.644 --> 01:16:49.438
-(jubilant shouts in distance)
-Yes, yes!

1333
01:16:49.521 --> 01:16:52.107
POSEIDON:
<i>Percy, wake up.</i>

1334
01:16:52.190 --> 01:16:54.776
<i>You need to escape. Wake up.</i>

1335
01:16:54.860 --> 01:16:56.194
You could really use a lotus flower.

1336
01:16:56.278 --> 01:16:57.487
I really don't want one.
Thank you.

1337
01:16:57.571 --> 01:16:59.406
-Just one.
-No.

1338
01:16:59.489 --> 01:17:01.491
(craps players shouting excitedly)

1339
01:17:02.618 --> 01:17:05.078
(roulette ball rattling)

1340
01:17:05.162 --> 01:17:07.164
(craps players cheering)

1341
01:17:14.921 --> 01:17:15.922
Another lotus flower?

1342
01:17:16.006 --> 01:17:17.424
-No.
-We insist.

1343
01:17:17.507 --> 01:17:20.469
I really don't want another lotus flower,
so please leave me alone.

1344
01:17:20.552 --> 01:17:21.970
Is there a problem, Mr. Jackson?

1345
01:17:24.640 --> 01:17:26.475
No, thank you.

1346
01:17:32.064 --> 01:17:34.066
Percy Jackson's awake.

1347
01:17:34.149 --> 01:17:35.651
("TiK ToK" by Ke$ha playing)

1348
01:17:35.734 --> 01:17:37.194
(girls giggling)

1349
01:17:37.277 --> 01:17:39.488
Excuse me.
Annabeth, Annabeth!

1350
01:17:39.571 --> 01:17:40.572
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
What are you doing with that?

1351
01:17:40.656 --> 01:17:41.657
-Don't eat that.
-What?!

1352
01:17:41.740 --> 01:17:42.741
We have to go now.

1353
01:17:42.824 --> 01:17:44.368
What do you mean?
We're having so much fun.

1354
01:17:44.451 --> 01:17:45.661
No, no, no, we're not having fun.

1355
01:17:45.744 --> 01:17:47.621
Grover! Grover! Wake up! Grover!

1356
01:17:47.704 --> 01:17:48.622
Come on. We gotta go!

1357
01:17:48.705 --> 01:17:51.833
What? Look, Perce,
your timing is terrible, okay?

1358
01:17:51.917 --> 01:17:54.294
Dude, we're heading to the chapel.
We're getting married!

1359
01:17:54.878 --> 01:17:56.421
-How romantic!
-No, no, no, no.

1360
01:17:56.505 --> 01:17:57.839
Wait, which one of y'all I propose to?

1361
01:17:57.923 --> 01:17:58.924
Oh!

1362
01:18:01.009 --> 01:18:02.636
Wake up!

1363
01:18:02.719 --> 01:18:05.097
Yo, man, you're such a buzzkill.

1364
01:18:05.180 --> 01:18:06.181
ANNABETH:
Percy, what's wrong with you?

1365
01:18:06.264 --> 01:18:07.265
Why are you doing this?

1366
01:18:07.349 --> 01:18:09.101
Both of you need to wake up now!

1367
01:18:09.184 --> 01:18:11.061
Look at me. Look at me.
You're in a trance, okay?

1368
01:18:11.144 --> 01:18:13.522
We're trapped! Listen to me.
If you eat the flowers,

1369
01:18:13.605 --> 01:18:15.816
you're never gonna
want to leave, okay?

1370
01:18:15.899 --> 01:18:17.484
We're gonna be stuck here forever!

1371
01:18:17.567 --> 01:18:18.819
Oh.

1372
01:18:20.237 --> 01:18:22.614
Oh, no. We gotta go.

1373
01:18:22.698 --> 01:18:23.740
-Okay, I see what you mean.
-Gotta get the green pearl.

1374
01:18:23.824 --> 01:18:24.825
All right, okay.

1375
01:18:30.789 --> 01:18:32.290
Hold it right there!

1376
01:18:32.374 --> 01:18:33.417
-Stop right there, sir!
-Stop where you are!

1377
01:18:33.500 --> 01:18:34.835
(grunting)

1378
01:18:34.918 --> 01:18:36.253
(crowd gasps)

1379
01:18:43.760 --> 01:18:45.220
(crowd gasps)

1380
01:18:47.931 --> 01:18:48.974
(grunting)

1381
01:18:53.061 --> 01:18:54.646
(gasps)
Oh!

1382
01:18:54.730 --> 01:18:56.189
James Dean, out of the way!

1383
01:18:56.273 --> 01:18:58.525
-Let's go, right!
-Car, car!

1384
01:18:58.608 --> 01:19:00.444
Come on, guys, car!

1385
01:19:01.987 --> 01:19:03.155
Get in!

1386
01:19:03.238 --> 01:19:04.698
Come on. Come on!

1387
01:19:04.781 --> 01:19:06.199
In the car, in the car!
Let's go! Keys!

1388
01:19:06.283 --> 01:19:07.993
-Got the keys.
-Come on!

1389
01:19:08.076 --> 01:19:09.119
PERCY:
Drive, drive, drive!

1390
01:19:09.202 --> 01:19:10.287
Okay, they're coming!
They're coming!

1391
01:19:10.370 --> 01:19:11.371
You want to start driving!

1392
01:19:11.455 --> 01:19:12.831
-GROVER: I got this.
-Go!

1393
01:19:12.914 --> 01:19:15.083
(tires screeching, engine revving)

1394
01:19:25.135 --> 01:19:26.970
(tires screeching)

1395
01:19:27.053 --> 01:19:28.472
(car horns honking)

1396
01:19:28.555 --> 01:19:30.056
(startled yell)

1397
01:19:33.101 --> 01:19:34.561
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

1398
01:19:34.644 --> 01:19:38.064
Now that's how you get out of a casino!
That's how you drive!

1399
01:19:38.148 --> 01:19:40.108
Of course.
Now that all makes sense.

1400
01:19:40.192 --> 01:19:41.193
What?

1401
01:19:41.276 --> 01:19:42.986
That was the lair of the lotus eaters.

1402
01:19:43.069 --> 01:19:45.655
They've been luring people
into their trap since ancient times.

1403
01:19:45.739 --> 01:19:48.533
Guys, look, tomorrow is June 21st.

1404
01:19:48.617 --> 01:19:51.453
PERCY: No, no, no, it can't be.
Today's the 15th.

1405
01:19:51.536 --> 01:19:53.538
ANNABETH:
No, tomorrow is the 21st.

1406
01:19:53.622 --> 01:19:55.290
We were in there for five days.

1407
01:19:55.373 --> 01:19:56.666
Felt like hours.

1408
01:19:56.750 --> 01:19:59.753
Then tomorrow's the solstice.
Our deadline is tomorrow at midnight.

1409
01:19:59.836 --> 01:20:02.255
Okay, look, we gotta move it.
Where's Hades?

1410
01:20:02.339 --> 01:20:04.007
Okay...

1411
01:20:06.802 --> 01:20:08.553
(quiet sizzling, crackling)

1412
01:20:08.637 --> 01:20:11.640
It's in... Hollywood.

1413
01:20:11.723 --> 01:20:13.141
GROVER: All right.

1414
01:20:13.225 --> 01:20:15.268
I can get us there in four hours.

1415
01:20:15.352 --> 01:20:17.062
Maybe three.

1416
01:20:17.145 --> 01:20:20.148
(engine revving, tires screeching)

1417
01:20:20.232 --> 01:20:21.983
(horns honking)

1418
01:20:44.798 --> 01:20:47.801
REPORTER (on radio): And now
the latest breaking news from KZLY.

1419
01:20:47.884 --> 01:20:49.970
An unprecedented
storm cloud has grown

1420
01:20:50.053 --> 01:20:52.222
to cover most of North America.

1421
01:20:52.305 --> 01:20:54.975
Authorities in several states
are ordering evacuations,

1422
01:20:55.058 --> 01:20:57.310
reporting severe weather conditions.

1423
01:21:03.066 --> 01:21:04.317
(all panting)

1424
01:21:04.401 --> 01:21:06.069
Don't slip. Watch your step.

1425
01:21:07.404 --> 01:21:10.532
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!
Wait, wait, wait. Hold it.

1426
01:21:15.287 --> 01:21:18.081
"Woe to all depraved souls."

1427
01:21:21.293 --> 01:21:23.128
(rumbling, cracking)

1428
01:21:44.441 --> 01:21:47.360
(debris clattering)

1429
01:21:47.444 --> 01:21:50.155
(sudden crash echoing)

1430
01:21:50.238 --> 01:21:52.532
Well, guess it ain't
no turning back now.

1431
01:21:52.616 --> 01:21:55.076
Yep. Looks like
we're stuck in here.

1432
01:21:55.160 --> 01:21:56.286
Yeah.

1433
01:22:07.380 --> 01:22:10.383
GROVER: Hey, Perce,
who's that creepy guy with the hoodie?

1434
01:22:10.467 --> 01:22:11.635
PERCY:
I don't know.

1435
01:22:12.719 --> 01:22:13.720
Let's find out.

1436
01:22:17.933 --> 01:22:19.434
Who are you?

1437
01:22:19.517 --> 01:22:21.561
We need to see Hades.

1438
01:22:21.645 --> 01:22:24.189
FERRYMAN:
The living are not permitted here.

1439
01:22:24.272 --> 01:22:26.942
Die and come back.

1440
01:22:27.943 --> 01:22:31.446
Okay, we won't (imitating voice)
"die and come back," but...

1441
01:22:31.529 --> 01:22:34.407
(sighs)
You know what?

1442
01:22:34.491 --> 01:22:37.410
-I think I know what he wants.
-What?

1443
01:22:37.494 --> 01:22:39.412
You gotta pay the ferryman.

1444
01:22:39.496 --> 01:22:41.373
Watch this.

1445
01:22:41.456 --> 01:22:43.375
Yo, my friend!
(chuckles)

1446
01:22:43.458 --> 01:22:45.502
What up? (chuckles)

1447
01:22:45.585 --> 01:22:47.128
Okay, guess not.

1448
01:22:47.212 --> 01:22:48.755
Look, you like dead people, right?

1449
01:22:48.838 --> 01:22:51.174
I got a few dead people
you might recognize.

1450
01:22:51.257 --> 01:22:54.219
Check this out.
Jackson, Grant.

1451
01:22:54.302 --> 01:22:57.514
And look who's joining
the party: Benjamin Franklin.

1452
01:22:57.597 --> 01:22:59.140
Yeah, you like that, don't you?

1453
01:22:59.224 --> 01:23:01.434
Look, you give us a boat ride,
you take the money,

1454
01:23:01.518 --> 01:23:04.479
and you get an interior decorator,
'cause it is too depressing in here.

1455
01:23:04.562 --> 01:23:06.272
A'ight? There you go.

1456
01:23:10.026 --> 01:23:11.611
(gasps)

1457
01:23:13.113 --> 01:23:15.532
GROVER:
That was $170!

1458
01:23:15.615 --> 01:23:17.951
Wait, wait, wait.
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

1459
01:23:18.034 --> 01:23:19.744
The drachma, the drachma.

1460
01:23:29.713 --> 01:23:30.922
Climb aboard.

1461
01:23:31.006 --> 01:23:33.466
Thanks for telling me, man. You're
burning money; we're in a recession.

1462
01:23:33.550 --> 01:23:35.260
-That's treason.
-Shut up. Shut up. Get on.

1463
01:23:46.980 --> 01:23:48.273
(rumbling)

1464
01:23:48.356 --> 01:23:51.693
(people screaming in distance)

1465
01:23:54.571 --> 01:23:57.032
FERRYMAN:
Welcome to the underworld.

1466
01:24:01.411 --> 01:24:03.246
What is all this?

1467
01:24:03.329 --> 01:24:05.081
(distant screaming and wailing)

1468
01:24:05.165 --> 01:24:08.501
The scrap heap of human misery.

1469
01:24:08.585 --> 01:24:10.962
Lost hopes and dreams.

1470
01:24:13.048 --> 01:24:15.133
Wishes that never came true.

1471
01:24:15.216 --> 01:24:17.052
(watch ticking)

1472
01:24:25.268 --> 01:24:29.522
(distant screams echoing)

1473
01:24:29.606 --> 01:24:33.109
FERRYMAN: All lives end
in suffering and tragedy.

1474
01:24:35.195 --> 01:24:37.197
(screams echoing)

1475
01:25:01.513 --> 01:25:03.640
This is as far as I go.

1476
01:25:20.657 --> 01:25:23.243
(growling echoes from distance)

1477
01:25:23.326 --> 01:25:25.078
Guys, do you hear that?

1478
01:25:25.161 --> 01:25:27.163
-PERCY: Yeah. What is that?
-GROVER: I don't know.

1479
01:25:28.873 --> 01:25:31.084
-(fierce growling)
-PERCY AND GROVER: Whoa!

1480
01:25:31.167 --> 01:25:32.418
Sit!

1481
01:25:32.502 --> 01:25:33.795
(growling)

1482
01:25:33.878 --> 01:25:36.047
-Annie, stab that thing!
-What are we going to do?

1483
01:25:36.131 --> 01:25:37.340
-(growling)
-(Annabeth grunts)

1484
01:25:37.423 --> 01:25:38.591
Stop it!

1485
01:25:38.675 --> 01:25:40.844
(speaking Greek)

1486
01:25:42.846 --> 01:25:44.430
What were those things?

1487
01:25:44.514 --> 01:25:45.598
Hellhounds.

1488
01:25:45.682 --> 01:25:46.808
GROVER:
Yeah.

1489
01:25:46.891 --> 01:25:49.018
Well, maybe you should feed 'em.

1490
01:25:49.602 --> 01:25:52.021
They sensed the presence
of another animal.

1491
01:25:52.105 --> 01:25:55.108
-Great. They smell goat.
-Hmm!

1492
01:25:55.191 --> 01:25:56.609
A satyr.

1493
01:25:59.070 --> 01:26:01.156
I haven't had a satyr...

1494
01:26:03.700 --> 01:26:04.993
...visit before.

1495
01:26:05.076 --> 01:26:06.870
HADES:
Persephone!

1496
01:26:06.953 --> 01:26:09.956
What could possibly
be taking so long?

1497
01:26:10.039 --> 01:26:11.583
Don't ignore me!

1498
01:26:11.666 --> 01:26:13.501
Or what?!

1499
01:26:13.585 --> 01:26:15.503
What will you do?

1500
01:26:15.587 --> 01:26:17.213
I'm already in Hell.

1501
01:26:38.151 --> 01:26:39.861
We have visitors.

1502
01:26:43.031 --> 01:26:44.616
Nephew.

1503
01:26:56.127 --> 01:26:57.545
Welcome.

1504
01:26:58.963 --> 01:27:01.216
You have your father's looks.

1505
01:27:02.550 --> 01:27:05.762
Always the, uh,
lucky side of the family.

1506
01:27:05.845 --> 01:27:07.430
(Grover laughs)

1507
01:27:07.513 --> 01:27:09.474
Wait. Wait a minute.
Wait a minute.

1508
01:27:09.557 --> 01:27:10.516
You're Hades?

1509
01:27:10.600 --> 01:27:12.310
-Yes.
-Oh, sorry.

1510
01:27:12.393 --> 01:27:15.521
I just didn't... I didn't expect you
to look like this, man.

1511
01:27:15.605 --> 01:27:17.023
Kind of stylish. I like it.

1512
01:27:17.106 --> 01:27:18.316
(chuckles)

1513
01:27:18.399 --> 01:27:20.151
Would you prefer that I looked like...

1514
01:27:20.235 --> 01:27:21.527
this?

1515
01:27:21.611 --> 01:27:22.946
(whooshing)

1516
01:27:23.029 --> 01:27:24.447
-GROVER: No! No! No!
-(growling)

1517
01:27:24.530 --> 01:27:25.573
Oh, no!

1518
01:27:25.657 --> 01:27:29.285
No! No, no. Look, stick to
the Mick Jagger thing. It works for you.

1519
01:27:29.369 --> 01:27:31.287
(growling)

1520
01:27:33.122 --> 01:27:34.749
(clears throat)

1521
01:27:34.832 --> 01:27:36.459
Hmph!

1522
01:27:36.542 --> 01:27:38.544
(scoffs)

1523
01:27:38.628 --> 01:27:41.923
HADES:
You're very brave coming here.

1524
01:27:42.006 --> 01:27:43.591
Come closer.

1525
01:27:46.803 --> 01:27:48.137
(whispering)
Hey. Perce.

1526
01:27:48.221 --> 01:27:50.723
HADES: I can see the look
of disgust in your eyes,

1527
01:27:50.807 --> 01:27:52.600
but this existence
was not of my choosing.

1528
01:27:52.684 --> 01:27:55.645
I was banished here
by Zeus and your father.

1529
01:27:55.728 --> 01:27:57.063
I'm damned.

1530
01:27:58.147 --> 01:28:00.149
My only chance
of getting out of this place

1531
01:28:00.233 --> 01:28:02.235
is to defeat my brothers
and take control of Olympus.

1532
01:28:02.318 --> 01:28:04.153
But, of course, um...

1533
01:28:05.405 --> 01:28:07.031
I'll need the bolt.

1534
01:28:07.615 --> 01:28:08.908
And I need my mother.

1535
01:28:08.992 --> 01:28:10.493
Then we have an understanding.

1536
01:28:10.576 --> 01:28:13.121
You give me the bolt,
and I'll give you your mother.

1537
01:28:18.293 --> 01:28:21.879
I need to tell you the truth.
I'm... I'm not the lightning thief.

1538
01:28:21.963 --> 01:28:23.798
I don't have the bolt.

1539
01:28:23.881 --> 01:28:25.300
I never did.

1540
01:28:27.176 --> 01:28:29.137
Why did you come here, then?

1541
01:28:30.972 --> 01:28:32.765
Well, I was hoping that...

1542
01:28:33.850 --> 01:28:36.894
when you saw that I wasn't the thief,
you'd let my mother go.

1543
01:28:36.978 --> 01:28:38.271
Yes.

1544
01:28:38.354 --> 01:28:40.398
Yes, but do you think I'm an idiot?

1545
01:28:41.482 --> 01:28:43.318
I'm Hades!

1546
01:28:43.401 --> 01:28:47.363
Now, give me the bolt,
or say good-bye to your mother.

1547
01:28:48.740 --> 01:28:49.741
(gasps)

1548
01:28:53.077 --> 01:28:54.954
(whooshing)

1549
01:29:06.924 --> 01:29:08.593
(gasps)

1550
01:29:11.929 --> 01:29:13.222
Percy.

1551
01:29:16.517 --> 01:29:19.062
(buzzing and crackling)

1552
01:29:20.938 --> 01:29:23.775
(sighs)
I thought I lost you forever.

1553
01:29:23.858 --> 01:29:25.526
No.

1554
01:29:30.156 --> 01:29:32.075
(crackling)

1555
01:29:37.914 --> 01:29:39.874
(crackling)

1556
01:29:43.920 --> 01:29:45.838
(crackling, rumbling)

1557
01:29:48.299 --> 01:29:51.052
Zeus' master bolt.

1558
01:29:52.720 --> 01:29:54.597
(Hades gasps in awe)

1559
01:29:55.431 --> 01:29:56.265
Liar.

1560
01:29:56.349 --> 01:29:59.268
I swear, I don't know
how that got there.

1561
01:29:59.352 --> 01:30:01.062
That's not even my shield.

1562
01:30:01.145 --> 01:30:03.606
ANNABETH:
No. Luke rigged it.

1563
01:30:03.689 --> 01:30:05.858
He put the bolt
in his shield and used us.

1564
01:30:05.942 --> 01:30:07.568
Luke stole the lightning bolt.

1565
01:30:07.652 --> 01:30:11.197
Um, I think we're done here.

1566
01:30:11.280 --> 01:30:12.907
Feed them to the souls.

1567
01:30:15.660 --> 01:30:17.829
-(clanking, rumbling)
-(gasping)

1568
01:30:19.705 --> 01:30:22.458
(whooshing)

1569
01:30:22.542 --> 01:30:25.128
(screaming, howling, screeching)

1570
01:30:26.963 --> 01:30:29.006
-Whoa! Whoa!
-We had a deal, all right?

1571
01:30:29.090 --> 01:30:31.217
You have the bolt. Just let us go.

1572
01:30:31.801 --> 01:30:33.219
Summon the hounds.

1573
01:30:34.303 --> 01:30:36.097
(speaks Greek)

1574
01:30:36.180 --> 01:30:38.516
-(hounds growling, snarling)
-No... no on the dogs.

1575
01:30:38.599 --> 01:30:39.684
(fierce growling)

1576
01:30:41.727 --> 01:30:43.813
Lassie, sit! Sit!

1577
01:30:43.896 --> 01:30:45.982
(hounds growling)

1578
01:30:46.065 --> 01:30:47.984
(souls screeching)

1579
01:30:50.111 --> 01:30:53.781
I... am going to be king of the gods.

1580
01:30:53.865 --> 01:30:55.324
-No!
-Stay back!

1581
01:30:55.408 --> 01:30:56.534
(growls)

1582
01:30:56.617 --> 01:30:58.536
-Back!
-Stay!

1583
01:30:58.619 --> 01:31:00.204
(jaws snap)

1584
01:31:02.248 --> 01:31:05.209
-Mmm... mmm.
-Mmm... mmm.

1585
01:31:07.295 --> 01:31:09.922
All right, come on...
(anxious laugh)

1586
01:31:10.006 --> 01:31:11.549
Come on. Give it back.

1587
01:31:11.632 --> 01:31:12.925
(yells)

1588
01:31:13.009 --> 01:31:14.385
(grunting)

1589
01:31:16.554 --> 01:31:18.473
(laughing)

1590
01:31:19.849 --> 01:31:21.642
(howling, screeching)

1591
01:31:21.726 --> 01:31:22.935
(speaks Greek)

1592
01:31:26.022 --> 01:31:28.816
(anxious gasping)

1593
01:31:28.900 --> 01:31:29.901
Bad dog!

1594
01:31:31.652 --> 01:31:33.404
(gasps)

1595
01:31:33.488 --> 01:31:35.990
He won't remember a thing!

1596
01:31:37.909 --> 01:31:39.535
Why'd you do that?

1597
01:31:39.619 --> 01:31:40.995
Because...

1598
01:31:41.996 --> 01:31:44.123
he's cruel and abusive!

1599
01:31:44.207 --> 01:31:46.667
The only thing I look forward to

1600
01:31:46.751 --> 01:31:49.754
is my allotted time
away from this hellhole.

1601
01:31:49.837 --> 01:31:55.718
A war of the gods would put
an end to that, and I'd be alone...

1602
01:31:55.801 --> 01:31:58.054
with only him...

1603
01:31:58.137 --> 01:31:59.555
forever.

1604
01:32:00.640 --> 01:32:01.974
(scoffs)

1605
01:32:02.058 --> 01:32:03.518
Go.

1606
01:32:03.601 --> 01:32:05.770
Take the bolt and your mother.

1607
01:32:06.354 --> 01:32:08.147
(crackling)

1608
01:32:08.231 --> 01:32:10.441
(switch clicks, blade rings)

1609
01:32:16.489 --> 01:32:17.907
Only three?

1610
01:32:19.742 --> 01:32:21.744
Oh, no.

1611
01:32:21.827 --> 01:32:23.788
PERSEPHONE:
There are four of you.

1612
01:32:23.871 --> 01:32:27.416
Each pearl transports
only a single person.

1613
01:32:27.500 --> 01:32:29.669
One of you will have to stay.

1614
01:32:30.753 --> 01:32:32.755
All right, I'll stay. You three go.

1615
01:32:32.838 --> 01:32:34.382
-SALLY: What? No!
-No. No, no, no.

1616
01:32:34.465 --> 01:32:37.134
I've achieved my quest.
I'm staying here.

1617
01:32:37.218 --> 01:32:38.344
ANNABETH: No. I've trained
for situations like this.

1618
01:32:38.427 --> 01:32:39.595
PERCY:
Neither of you are st...

1619
01:32:39.679 --> 01:32:41.722
Guys, guys, knock it off.

1620
01:32:41.806 --> 01:32:44.725
-I'm staying because I'm the protector.
-Grover, come on.

1621
01:32:44.809 --> 01:32:47.603
Look, man, I don't want
to hear it. Just go.

1622
01:32:47.687 --> 01:32:48.980
It's my duty.

1623
01:32:50.481 --> 01:32:51.899
It's what I'm meant for.

1624
01:32:51.983 --> 01:32:54.026
We'll come back for you.

1625
01:32:54.610 --> 01:32:58.447
I'll take very good care of him.

1626
01:32:59.907 --> 01:33:01.576
All right, now, move it, guys.

1627
01:33:01.659 --> 01:33:04.662
Each of you step on the pearl
and concentrate on where you want to go.

1628
01:33:04.745 --> 01:33:05.871
Take this.

1629
01:33:07.206 --> 01:33:08.583
To Olympus.

1630
01:33:14.171 --> 01:33:16.090
(thunder rumbles)

1631
01:33:16.173 --> 01:33:18.634
(hissing, whooshing)

1632
01:33:28.227 --> 01:33:31.022
(hissing, whooshing fade)

1633
01:33:37.903 --> 01:33:39.155
(bleats)

1634
01:33:39.238 --> 01:33:40.531
(muffled grunt)

1635
01:33:40.615 --> 01:33:41.657
Whew!

1636
01:33:49.790 --> 01:33:51.626
(deep whooshing)

1637
01:34:00.551 --> 01:34:03.095
(crackling)

1638
01:34:06.265 --> 01:34:09.727
(thunder crashing)

1639
01:34:09.810 --> 01:34:11.646
Hey. Look.

1640
01:34:11.729 --> 01:34:14.106
(wind whistling)

1641
01:34:17.360 --> 01:34:19.695
Zeus and Poseidon
preparing for battle.

1642
01:34:19.779 --> 01:34:21.322
No...

1643
01:34:21.405 --> 01:34:23.157
No, no, this isn't the right place.

1644
01:34:23.240 --> 01:34:24.575
This isn't Olympus.
This is...

1645
01:34:24.659 --> 01:34:26.327
this is the Empire State Building.

1646
01:34:26.410 --> 01:34:29.372
Percy! The entrance
to Olympus is there!

1647
01:34:29.455 --> 01:34:31.874
Well, there's ten minutes
till midnight. Let's move.

1648
01:34:31.957 --> 01:34:33.918
LUKE: Percy Jackson!

1649
01:34:34.001 --> 01:34:36.003
(wings fluttering)

1650
01:34:40.675 --> 01:34:43.260
Well, you weren't supposed
to make it out alive.

1651
01:34:44.845 --> 01:34:47.181
I can't let you take
that bolt to Olympus.

1652
01:34:48.516 --> 01:34:50.226
I'm the lightning thief.

1653
01:34:50.726 --> 01:34:53.688
You hid the bolt
in my shield? Why?

1654
01:34:53.771 --> 01:34:58.067
Well, when you said you were
going to the underworld, it hit me.

1655
01:34:58.150 --> 01:35:01.153
That is the perfect opportunity
to get the bolt to Hades.

1656
01:35:01.737 --> 01:35:03.197
Why would you do that?

1657
01:35:03.280 --> 01:35:05.783
To bring Olympus crumbling down.

1658
01:35:06.283 --> 01:35:08.202
SALLY: Percy, let's go.

1659
01:35:08.703 --> 01:35:10.371
Let's go.

1660
01:35:10.454 --> 01:35:14.500
Well, it's too late, 'cause I'm
returning the bolt to Zeus right now.

1661
01:35:14.583 --> 01:35:16.544
Not before midnight.

1662
01:35:17.670 --> 01:35:19.296
(Luke grunting)

1663
01:35:19.380 --> 01:35:20.798
(yells, groans)

1664
01:35:22.508 --> 01:35:24.009
(growling)

1665
01:35:26.804 --> 01:35:29.098
(crackles, sizzles)

1666
01:35:29.181 --> 01:35:30.182
(grunting)

1667
01:35:30.266 --> 01:35:32.560
(groaning)

1668
01:35:34.895 --> 01:35:36.564
(fierce yell)

1669
01:35:39.483 --> 01:35:42.445
-(knife whooshing)
-(both grunting)

1670
01:35:45.448 --> 01:35:46.449
(grunts in pain)

1671
01:35:51.162 --> 01:35:52.830
-You all right?
-Yeah.

1672
01:35:54.790 --> 01:35:58.002
PERCY: Luke, why do you
want a war of the gods?

1673
01:35:59.044 --> 01:36:00.254
Control.

1674
01:36:01.464 --> 01:36:03.507
They've been in power for too long.

1675
01:36:03.591 --> 01:36:07.136
I say it's time for our generation
to take over,

1676
01:36:07.219 --> 01:36:09.680
remold the world in our image.

1677
01:36:09.764 --> 01:36:11.557
A world of new heroes.

1678
01:36:11.640 --> 01:36:13.267
You're no hero.

1679
01:36:14.477 --> 01:36:15.603
(Percy and Annabeth gasp)

1680
01:36:20.065 --> 01:36:21.859
(all yell)

1681
01:36:21.942 --> 01:36:23.152
(chuckles)

1682
01:36:24.195 --> 01:36:25.696
(screaming)

1683
01:36:27.406 --> 01:36:29.283
(yelling, gasping)

1684
01:36:30.326 --> 01:36:31.994
-Mom, are you all right?
-Yeah.

1685
01:36:32.077 --> 01:36:33.579
(whooshing)

1686
01:36:33.662 --> 01:36:35.247
Stay here.

1687
01:36:35.331 --> 01:36:38.292
(panting)

1688
01:36:49.220 --> 01:36:51.972
(helicopter approaching)

1689
01:36:55.434 --> 01:36:56.769
(crackling)

1690
01:36:56.852 --> 01:36:57.895
PERCY: Luke!

1691
01:36:58.938 --> 01:37:00.564
(grunting)

1692
01:37:04.109 --> 01:37:05.277
Whoa...!

1693
01:37:07.404 --> 01:37:08.697
(growls, yells)

1694
01:37:14.328 --> 01:37:15.871
(yells)

1695
01:37:17.748 --> 01:37:18.916
(fierce grunt)

1696
01:37:18.999 --> 01:37:20.668
Whoa!

1697
01:37:23.838 --> 01:37:24.964
(boom echoing)

1698
01:37:34.265 --> 01:37:35.266
Whoa!

1699
01:37:37.184 --> 01:37:38.519
(gasping)

1700
01:37:47.278 --> 01:37:48.529
(yells, grunts)

1701
01:37:53.450 --> 01:37:54.702
(grunts)

1702
01:38:06.005 --> 01:38:07.172
(grunts)

1703
01:38:09.967 --> 01:38:11.093
Aah! Oh!

1704
01:38:13.429 --> 01:38:15.514
(gasping)

1705
01:38:15.598 --> 01:38:17.182
(yelling)

1706
01:38:18.726 --> 01:38:21.896
No! Oh... oh...!

1707
01:38:21.979 --> 01:38:23.480
(yells, grunting)

1708
01:38:23.564 --> 01:38:25.733
(groaning in pain)

1709
01:38:27.443 --> 01:38:28.527
(spits)

1710
01:38:28.611 --> 01:38:30.654
(grunts, pants)

1711
01:38:34.700 --> 01:38:36.368
(crackles, sizzles)

1712
01:38:39.997 --> 01:38:41.749
Maybe they were wrong.

1713
01:38:43.542 --> 01:38:45.419
Maybe you're no son of Poseidon.

1714
01:38:50.674 --> 01:38:51.717
Hmm.

1715
01:38:51.800 --> 01:38:52.676
(grunts)

1716
01:38:52.760 --> 01:38:53.844
(creaking)

1717
01:38:53.928 --> 01:38:55.888
(bolts exploding)

1718
01:39:02.478 --> 01:39:04.563
-(grunts)
-(booming)

1719
01:39:18.535 --> 01:39:20.579
(panting)

1720
01:39:23.123 --> 01:39:24.124
(grunts)

1721
01:39:29.380 --> 01:39:31.590
(muffled yelling)

1722
01:39:31.674 --> 01:39:33.384
(grunts)

1723
01:39:33.467 --> 01:39:36.345
(electrical crackling)

1724
01:39:46.563 --> 01:39:48.774
(Luke coughing, gagging)

1725
01:39:52.236 --> 01:39:53.278
(spits)

1726
01:39:53.362 --> 01:39:55.614
(panting)

1727
01:39:55.698 --> 01:39:57.449
(buzzing, crackling)

1728
01:39:57.533 --> 01:39:59.660
(gasping)

1729
01:40:03.247 --> 01:40:05.499
(panting)

1730
01:40:07.376 --> 01:40:10.087
(burbling, whooshing)

1731
01:40:10.170 --> 01:40:11.296
Yeah.

1732
01:40:11.380 --> 01:40:12.715
(trident rings)

1733
01:40:12.798 --> 01:40:14.967
I think I am the son of Poseidon.

1734
01:40:15.050 --> 01:40:16.677
(both grunt)

1735
01:40:16.760 --> 01:40:18.429
(grunts, yells)

1736
01:40:19.930 --> 01:40:21.724
Whoa...!

1737
01:40:21.807 --> 01:40:24.518
(bolt crackling)

1738
01:40:27.813 --> 01:40:29.815
(fluttering)

1739
01:40:31.025 --> 01:40:34.486
(sirens wailing in distance)

1740
01:40:34.570 --> 01:40:36.280
(grunts)

1741
01:40:37.573 --> 01:40:41.118
He's got the bolt! Come on!
Let's move! We've got two minutes.

1742
01:40:46.206 --> 01:40:47.499
(electrical whirring)

1743
01:41:00.929 --> 01:41:02.514
(sudden rumbling)

1744
01:41:07.269 --> 01:41:10.189
(high-speed whirring)

1745
01:41:10.272 --> 01:41:11.940
(explosive boom)

1746
01:41:12.024 --> 01:41:14.985
(all panting)

1747
01:41:15.069 --> 01:41:16.945
(thunder rumbles)

1748
01:41:23.994 --> 01:41:24.870
Olympus.

1749
01:41:31.502 --> 01:41:34.755
Percy, I can't get through.
You've got to go!

1750
01:41:44.848 --> 01:41:46.683
(gods arguing)

1751
01:41:52.106 --> 01:41:53.315
Silence!

1752
01:41:53.398 --> 01:41:55.275
(arguments quiet)

1753
01:42:06.120 --> 01:42:08.831
ZEUS:
It is almost midnight.

1754
01:42:08.914 --> 01:42:10.624
This was predestined.

1755
01:42:10.707 --> 01:42:12.251
You wanted this battle!

1756
01:42:12.334 --> 01:42:13.961
You have only yourself to blame!

1757
01:42:14.044 --> 01:42:15.921
ATHENA:
Please!

1758
01:42:16.004 --> 01:42:18.799
Let's be rational.
War is not the answer!

1759
01:42:22.344 --> 01:42:23.846
Time has run out.

1760
01:42:23.929 --> 01:42:25.180
PERCY:
Wait!

1761
01:42:26.181 --> 01:42:27.891
Wait! Wait!

1762
01:42:28.976 --> 01:42:30.144
Wow.

1763
01:42:36.817 --> 01:42:38.735
My name is Percy Jackson,

1764
01:42:38.819 --> 01:42:41.947
and I think you might be looking for this.

1765
01:42:52.833 --> 01:42:55.377
(bolt sizzling, crackling)

1766
01:42:58.881 --> 01:43:01.425
Give me the bolt, lightning thief.

1767
01:43:03.969 --> 01:43:07.431
(bolt sizzling, crackling)

1768
01:43:07.514 --> 01:43:10.309
(thunder cracking)

1769
01:43:13.228 --> 01:43:15.689
You're wise to betray your father.

1770
01:43:15.772 --> 01:43:17.441
I didn't steal it.

1771
01:43:17.524 --> 01:43:20.027
And I have no connection
to Poseidon.

1772
01:43:21.111 --> 01:43:26.116
But tell me, if you didn't steal it,
then who did?

1773
01:43:26.200 --> 01:43:29.161
Luke, son of Hermes.

1774
01:43:32.915 --> 01:43:34.750
You see, he was angry at you.

1775
01:43:35.334 --> 01:43:36.668
All of you.

1776
01:43:36.752 --> 01:43:39.922
He wanted you to destroy yourselves.

1777
01:43:50.849 --> 01:43:52.309
You have done well.

1778
01:44:05.530 --> 01:44:07.241
Let there be peace.

1779
01:44:07.741 --> 01:44:09.368
(exhales)

1780
01:44:12.037 --> 01:44:13.038
Hi, Mom.

1781
01:44:14.122 --> 01:44:15.249
Annabeth.

1782
01:44:15.332 --> 01:44:18.001
ATHENA:
I am so proud of you.

1783
01:44:20.837 --> 01:44:24.383
Zeus, I have a good friend.

1784
01:44:24.466 --> 01:44:28.303
He's a satyr named Grover.

1785
01:44:28.387 --> 01:44:30.180
He's my protector.

1786
01:44:30.264 --> 01:44:32.516
And the only reason why
we escaped the underworld

1787
01:44:32.599 --> 01:44:34.935
is because he stayed behind.

1788
01:44:36.270 --> 01:44:39.314
And now you expect me
to bring him back.

1789
01:44:42.276 --> 01:44:43.610
Very well.

1790
01:44:43.694 --> 01:44:46.029
(relieved sigh)

1791
01:44:46.113 --> 01:44:49.950
I believe this assembly's
business here is finished.

1792
01:44:51.743 --> 01:44:53.078
Brother, please.

1793
01:44:54.079 --> 01:44:55.831
I need to speak with him.

1794
01:44:59.334 --> 01:45:01.211
Just this once.

1795
01:45:12.848 --> 01:45:14.683
I'll meet you outside.

1796
01:45:25.319 --> 01:45:27.487
I'm not expecting you to forgive me.

1797
01:45:29.239 --> 01:45:31.700
But I want you to know
that I'm grateful.

1798
01:45:31.783 --> 01:45:33.493
I didn't do it for you.

1799
01:45:34.870 --> 01:45:36.163
I did it to save Mom.

1800
01:45:41.877 --> 01:45:44.004
(water rushing)

1801
01:45:44.087 --> 01:45:47.049
Please, we don't have much time.

1802
01:45:50.135 --> 01:45:52.054
How old was I...

1803
01:45:52.137 --> 01:45:53.555
when you left?

1804
01:45:54.389 --> 01:45:55.390
Seven months.

1805
01:45:56.975 --> 01:45:59.811
Look, I didn't need you
there all the time,

1806
01:45:59.895 --> 01:46:01.104
but what...

1807
01:46:02.606 --> 01:46:05.108
I would've liked to have
seen you just once.

1808
01:46:08.195 --> 01:46:10.364
Why didn't you ever come back?

1809
01:46:15.911 --> 01:46:17.412
I wanted to.

1810
01:46:19.873 --> 01:46:21.583
When I was with you and your mother,

1811
01:46:21.666 --> 01:46:25.045
I became less concerned
with my responsibilities.

1812
01:46:25.128 --> 01:46:27.255
I was becoming human.

1813
01:46:29.174 --> 01:46:31.051
And that's a bad thing?

1814
01:46:31.134 --> 01:46:33.845
For a god?
Zeus thought so.

1815
01:46:33.929 --> 01:46:35.430
That's why he passed the law

1816
01:46:35.514 --> 01:46:38.558
preventing gods from ever
having contact with their children.

1817
01:46:40.352 --> 01:46:42.187
That was because of you?

1818
01:46:46.525 --> 01:46:48.402
But I was always watching over you.

1819
01:46:50.237 --> 01:46:53.407
Just because you didn't see me
doesn't mean that I wasn't there.

1820
01:46:55.117 --> 01:46:58.036
When you were troubled,
I tried to help.

1821
01:46:59.704 --> 01:47:00.747
I heard you.

1822
01:47:02.082 --> 01:47:05.419
I know I'm not the father
you always wanted.

1823
01:47:05.502 --> 01:47:08.880
But if you ever need me,
I'll be there for you.

1824
01:47:08.964 --> 01:47:10.132
In your thoughts.

1825
01:47:11.133 --> 01:47:13.051
And in your dreams.

1826
01:47:14.970 --> 01:47:16.638
I'll stand by you, Percy.

1827
01:47:17.973 --> 01:47:19.182
Always.

1828
01:47:34.990 --> 01:47:36.783
(sighs)

1829
01:47:45.500 --> 01:47:47.794
You can come visit me anytime.

1830
01:47:47.878 --> 01:47:51.173
Just promise me that I don't have to
see that loser Gabe ever again.

1831
01:47:51.256 --> 01:47:52.799
I kicked him out.

1832
01:47:52.883 --> 01:47:56.887
Yeah, he's gone.
He's out of our lives forever.

1833
01:47:57.888 --> 01:47:58.889
Finally.

1834
01:47:58.972 --> 01:47:59.973
(chuckles)

1835
01:48:04.853 --> 01:48:05.854
Oh.

1836
01:48:05.937 --> 01:48:06.938
(sighs)

1837
01:48:07.022 --> 01:48:09.232
-Gonna miss you.
-You, too.

1838
01:48:16.865 --> 01:48:18.033
Percy...

1839
01:48:19.534 --> 01:48:21.036
This is where you belong.

1840
01:48:32.672 --> 01:48:34.007
-Good job, man.
-Nice, Perce.

1841
01:48:35.133 --> 01:48:36.760
Ready!

1842
01:48:36.843 --> 01:48:38.136
Aim!

1843
01:48:38.220 --> 01:48:39.971
-Whoa, Perce, watch out!
-Whoa, hey!

1844
01:48:40.055 --> 01:48:41.681
Whoa, you guys gonna kill
the man who saved the world?

1845
01:48:41.765 --> 01:48:43.350
Great job. All you guys
take a lunch break.

1846
01:48:43.433 --> 01:48:45.435
Thank you.
(chuckles)

1847
01:48:45.519 --> 01:48:47.354
So the conquering hero
returns triumphant.

1848
01:48:47.437 --> 01:48:48.730
Grover.

1849
01:48:48.813 --> 01:48:51.107
Hey, you notice anything
different about me?

1850
01:48:51.191 --> 01:48:52.192
No.

1851
01:48:53.527 --> 01:48:54.861
You sure?

1852
01:48:54.945 --> 01:48:57.239
Anything that's improved about me?

1853
01:48:57.322 --> 01:48:59.783
No, what?
You've been working out, huh?

1854
01:48:59.866 --> 01:49:02.118
What, you get a new cologne?
You smell good.

1855
01:49:02.202 --> 01:49:03.828
Look, man, I got my horns!

1856
01:49:03.912 --> 01:49:05.580
Oh! I was seeing them
the whole time.

1857
01:49:05.664 --> 01:49:07.040
-Look at that thing.
-(laughs)

1858
01:49:07.123 --> 01:49:08.375
Got little horns in your head.

1859
01:49:08.458 --> 01:49:10.001
-Right? Zeus came through.
-Crazy.

1860
01:49:10.085 --> 01:49:11.795
-Wow.
-Now I'm Senior Protector,

1861
01:49:11.878 --> 01:49:13.004
First Class, baby.

1862
01:49:13.088 --> 01:49:15.423
Congratulations.
Definitely earned them.

1863
01:49:15.507 --> 01:49:17.008
Thank you, man.

1864
01:49:17.092 --> 01:49:18.260
-(Grover laughs)
-Yeah.

1865
01:49:18.843 --> 01:49:22.430
CHIRON: Keep moving! Keep moving!
Don't lose interest!

1866
01:49:22.514 --> 01:49:26.685
One foot in front of the other, and
the next thing you know, you're running!

1867
01:49:28.812 --> 01:49:29.896
Percy.

1868
01:49:33.108 --> 01:49:34.651
You left the camp.

1869
01:49:34.734 --> 01:49:36.319
You disobeyed my orders.

1870
01:49:37.404 --> 01:49:39.990
Yeah, about that. Um...

1871
01:49:40.073 --> 01:49:42.325
Which is why...

1872
01:49:42.409 --> 01:49:44.035
you're my favorite student.

1873
01:49:45.537 --> 01:49:47.622
You can receive
all the training in the world,

1874
01:49:47.706 --> 01:49:51.293
but, ultimately,
you have to follow your instincts.

1875
01:49:51.376 --> 01:49:53.128
Grace under pressure.

1876
01:49:56.631 --> 01:49:58.091
All right.

1877
01:49:58.174 --> 01:50:00.343
Time to train. Go suit up.

1878
01:50:00.427 --> 01:50:02.387
You might be a big shot
on Olympus,

1879
01:50:02.470 --> 01:50:04.806
but down here, you're still
just one of my students.

1880
01:50:05.307 --> 01:50:06.308
Move it.

1881
01:50:09.394 --> 01:50:11.229
Nice horns, Grover.

1882
01:50:11.313 --> 01:50:12.897
-GROVER: I'm serious, man.
-Okay.

1883
01:50:12.981 --> 01:50:15.650
We talked. We wooed. We dined.
We had a great time!

1884
01:50:15.734 --> 01:50:17.110
Well, I'm happy for you, you know.

1885
01:50:17.193 --> 01:50:18.945
Persephone might really
like me. I'm serious.

1886
01:50:24.993 --> 01:50:27.329
I think you can handle
this one on your own.

1887
01:50:27.412 --> 01:50:29.080
Whew. Uh-huh.

1888
01:50:29.164 --> 01:50:30.540
All right, Perce.

1889
01:50:30.624 --> 01:50:32.250
(swords clanging, Annabeth grunting)

1890
01:50:32.334 --> 01:50:33.752
(anxious sigh)

1891
01:50:33.835 --> 01:50:35.003
-Hey, Perce, awesome job.
-Thanks...

1892
01:50:35.086 --> 01:50:36.087
-Good job.
-Thanks.

1893
01:50:36.171 --> 01:50:37.422
Good job, buddy.

1894
01:50:37.505 --> 01:50:40.175
(swords clanging, Annabeth grunting)

1895
01:50:40.258 --> 01:50:41.760
Good job.

1896
01:50:45.930 --> 01:50:48.141
(grunt, thud)

1897
01:50:48.224 --> 01:50:50.518
(groans)

1898
01:50:50.602 --> 01:50:52.354
Who's next?

1899
01:50:57.859 --> 01:51:00.028
I think I'd like to give it a shot.

1900
01:51:11.915 --> 01:51:13.124
Welcome home.

1901
01:51:19.381 --> 01:51:22.217
Whoa, whoa! Wait!

1902
01:51:22.300 --> 01:51:25.428
First rule of battle strategy:

1903
01:51:25.512 --> 01:51:28.056
don't ever let your opponent distract you.

1904
01:51:44.030 --> 01:51:45.073
(grunting)

1905
01:51:54.040 --> 01:51:57.377
<i>(music playing)</i>

1906
01:53:08.114 --> 01:53:09.324
(pounding on door)

1907
01:53:09.407 --> 01:53:12.035
GABE:
Sally, open the door!

1908
01:53:12.118 --> 01:53:13.870
Open up!

1909
01:53:17.332 --> 01:53:19.167
-You changed the locks?
-Yes.

1910
01:53:20.210 --> 01:53:23.421
So here's your junk.
You can let yourself out.

1911
01:53:25.048 --> 01:53:28.384
How am I supposed to move
all this stuff by myself?

1912
01:53:28.468 --> 01:53:29.677
Deal with it.

1913
01:53:35.350 --> 01:53:36.976
I need a beer.

1914
01:53:40.814 --> 01:53:42.065
What?!

1915
01:53:42.148 --> 01:53:43.233
"Do not op..."

1916
01:53:47.403 --> 01:53:48.988
That little brat.

1917
01:53:50.365 --> 01:53:52.158
I may not live here anymore...

1918
01:53:53.409 --> 01:53:55.662
but I'm still the king of this castle.

1919
01:53:58.373 --> 01:54:01.125
(hissing)

1920
01:54:04.462 --> 01:54:06.548
(crackling)

1921
01:54:09.592 --> 01:54:11.553
<i>(noble orchestral theme playing)</i>

1922
01:55:40.558 --> 01:55:42.644
<i>(mysterious theme playing)</i>

1923
01:57:17.321 --> 01:57:21.325
<i>(slow, melancholy theme playing)</i>

1924
01:57:50.772 --> 01:57:54.942
<i>(theme crescendos)</i>

1925
01:58:05.787 --> 01:58:09.707
<i>(theme quiets)</i>

